62 Insurance on oath 17 Clarification of the facts 171 Scope 18 Separate statement 181 Procedure, content and period 1811 Procedure 1812 Cont old of the separate determination 1813 Relevant financial year, determination year, assessment period 1814 Downstream intermediate companies 1815 Reimbursements according to \u00a7 11 Paragraph 2 and 3 AStG 182 Local tax office 183 Declaration on the separate and possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Uniform determination 20 Relationship to double taxation agreements 21 Application regulations Text of Annex 1: Text of Annex 2: Text of Annex 3: The individual text numbers and headings refer to the relevant provision of the AStG and the corresponding paragraphs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "76 = Section 7 (6) AStG; Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8151 = sub-item to Section 8 (1) No. 5 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If no statement has been made about a paragraph, the text number is also missing (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "No statement on Section 7 (5) AStG, so no no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Annex 1: Findings about important areas with low tax rates, preferential rates or tax exemptions for legal persons Annex 2: Findings about areas with a normal rate of income tax for legal persons Annex 3: Schemes for determining the tax bases for the application of \u00a7\u00a7 7-14 AStG With reference to the The result of the discussions with the representatives of the highest tax authorities of the federal states applies to the application of the external tax law: 0 Relationship of the external tax law to other tax regulations The external tax law supplements the provisions that regulate the taxation of foreign relations in the tax code and other tax laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The agreements to avoid double taxation (double taxation agreement / DTA) take precedence over the external tax law as well as the other tax laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 International interdependencies10 Application of the principles for the examination of income accruals at internationally affiliated companies (administrative principles) 101 For the term \"related person\", the standard of correction (principle of external behavior) and the treatment of correction amounts, the \"principles for checking income accrual apply to internationally affiliated companies (administrative principles) \"of the BMF letter of 23 February 1983 - IV C 5 - S-1341 - 4/83 -, BStBl 1983 I, 218)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When applying these principles, it should be noted that the interdependence through identity of interests (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1327 of the Administrative Principles) is not justified solely by the fact that all participants have an equal interest in commercial transactions and the taxpayer and his business partners intend to make a profit with the same or similar activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Rather, what is required is a connection of interests, by virtue of which the taxpayer receives the benefit of the related person as his own benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "102 The administrative principles apply not only to business relationships between affiliated companies, but also to all other business relationships within the meaning of Section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The delimitation clauses of the double taxation agreements (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "12 of the administrative principles) must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The regulation on the subsequent compensation of reduced income (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "83 of the Administrative Principles) is also to be applied to cases in which income that does not belong to profit income is corrected and the reduction in income is compensated for by domestic taxable transactions (see BFH judgment of 30 May 1990 BStBl II, 875)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "11 Correction111 Paragraph 1 (1) of the AStG contains a legal basis and the \"yardstick for external behavior\" for corrections of income in cross-border business relationships (\"principle of external behavior\")"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "112 Paragraph 1 of the AStG does not affect other provisions on correction and gives them priority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is especially true for hidden profit distributions and hidden deposits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the transfer of assets is only to be treated as a hidden contribution if equity is also created under foreign company law (see BFH judgment of 30 May 1990 BStBl II, 875)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, corrections are to be based exclusively on \u00a7 1 AStG if a domestic taxpayer grants a foreign subsidiary uses or services without adequate remuneration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the necessary correction according to the standard of external behavior cannot be made via a hidden deposit (see BFH decision of October 26, 1987 BStBl 1988 II, 348)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "14 Business relationships141 Relationships between related parties are always business-related if the provisions on the taxation of income from agriculture and forestry, from commercial operations, from self-employed work and the provisions of Section 1 (4) AStG apply to the underlying activities of the domestic taxpayer or the related person from renting and leasing are to be applied (basic activities)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also always includes the activities of corporations, insofar as their income is to be treated as income from commercial operations in accordance with Section 8 (2) KStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that the related person is or would be subject to limited taxation with this income within the meaning of Section 1 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Examples: The granting of a private loan by a domestic taxpayer to a foreign real estate company closely related to him falls under Section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether their real estate is in Germany or abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It also makes no difference whether the company generates income from renting and leasing or business income; Both types of income are income from basic activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The granting of loans from private funds for private use or to generate capital income does not fall under Section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "142 In contrast, shareholding relationships are not business relationships within the meaning of Section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This applies u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "for the corporate relations of the partner of a partnership to this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "143 All cross-border business relationships within the meaning of Section 1 (4) AStG fall under Section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It makes no difference whether the taxpayer and the persons with whom these business relationships exist are subject to unlimited or limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\"Business relationships with foreign countries\" also exist in the case of transactions between the domestic permanent establishment of an unlimited taxpayer and the foreign permanent establishment of another person with unlimited tax liability close to him; the domestic permanent establishment of an unlimited taxpayer and the foreign permanent establishment of an intermediate company in which the unlimited taxpayer participates; the domestic Permanent establishment of a person with limited tax liability and the foreign permanent establishment of a closely related other person with limited tax liability; domestic and foreign partnerships, communities and similar entities with identical participation in whole or in part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "144 For assessment periods up to and including 1991 (Article 7 Site Security Act in conjunction with Section 21 Paragraph 4 Sentence 2 AStG), Section 1 AStG is only applicable to relationships that led to profit determination income for the taxpayer himself (see BFH judgment of 5 December 1990 BStBl 1991 II, 287)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2 Change of residence to low-tax areas20 Scope of application201 Extended limited tax liability2011 Sections 2 to 5 AStG extend the limited tax liability for people who have moved to low-tax areas and are no longer subject to unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2012 Anyone who meets the personal requirements of \u00a7 2 AStG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "21), is subject to limited income tax liability in the year of the change of residence and for the following ten years, provided that he is resident in a foreign area during this period and is not taxed there or is only taxed at a low rate or is not resident in any area (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "22) and has significant economic interests in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the requirements of nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 are not given, the limited tax liability according to Section 1 (4) EStG remains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Limited and extended limited tax liability can also switch, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "if a taxpayer first moves his domicile to a non-low tax area and later from there to a low tax area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2013 The extended limited tax liability comes into effect despite the existence of the provisions in No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisites listed in 2012 are not applicable to assessment periods in which the total taxable income does not exceed DM 32,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free capital gains, with the exception of profits exempted under Section 16 (4) sentence 3 EStG (Section 50 (1) sentence 5 EStG), income exempted under a DTA or the foreign activity decree, and tax-free income do not count towards the total taxable income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxes deductible according to Section 50 (6) EStG must be taken into account when determining the total taxable income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A loss compensation between positive and negative domestic income must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Special expenses, extraordinary burdens and tariff allowances within the meaning of Section 50 Paragraph 1 Clause 5 EStG, on the other hand, cannot be deducted, unless they are cross-border commuters, to whom Section 50 Paragraph 4 EStG applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In addition, Section 50 (1) sentences 6 and 7 of the Income Tax Act (EStG) must be observed in the case of employees with extended limited tax liability who receive income from non-self-employed work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "202 Effects of double taxation agreements 2021 As long as the taxpayer is resident in a foreign area for which a double taxation agreement exists, the following applies: Income and assets for which the area concerned (country of residence) has exclusive taxation rights under the double taxation agreement are not subject to the extended limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Does the agreement limit the German tax eligibility for certain income to a maximum rate (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in the case of dividends), the tax on this income may only be levied up to this limit even with the extended limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the German tax authorization is not limited under the DBA (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income from a permanent establishment located in Germany or income from immovable property located in Germany), the tax rate for the extended limited taxable income is based on world income in these cases as well"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: A taxpayer relocates to a low-tax double taxation country, but continues to have a commercial establishment in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisites for an extended limited tax liability exist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to the permanent establishment article of this DBA, the Federal Republic of Germany has a right to tax the permanent establishment income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When determining the tax rate to be applied to the permanent establishment income, all income of the taxpayer must be taken as a basis (Section 2 (5) sentence 1 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2022 It must always be checked whether the taxpayer is actually entitled to the treaty, in particular whether he is resident in the country concerned within the meaning of the treaty"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Doubts may arise in the information"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "be clarified in the mutual agreement procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2023 According to the DTA Switzerland, the following must be observed: Article 4 Paragraph 4 The restrictions of the agreement for the year of departure and for the following five years do not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply to Swiss nationals and persons who, within the meaning of the last sentence of Article 4 (4) of the Agreement, have an employment relationship in Switzerland or who are cross-border commuters (Article 15 (4); from 1994 Article 15a DTA) due to marriage to a Swiss citizen Citizens have moved to Switzerland (mutual agreement with Switzerland; see BMF letter of April 1, 1977 IV C 6 - S-1301 Schz - 38/77)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "During the aforementioned period, a tax levied in Switzerland in accordance with Article 4 Paragraph 4 of the Agreement is to be offset against the tax that is levied in addition to the tax that would have been determined without the application of Article 4 Paragraph 4"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Article 4 Paragraph 6 a A person who is to be regarded as resident in Switzerland under the Agreement and who is not subject to the generally levied Swiss taxes on all income from the Federal Republic of Germany that is generally taxable under Swiss tax law is deemed not to be resident in Switzerland"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The agreement therefore does not apply to these persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2024 According to No. 17 of the Protocol to Articles 24 and 6 to 22 of the DBA-Ialien 1989, German citizens who are subject to the extended limited tax liability according to \u00a7 2 AStG can have domestic income and assets located in Germany independently of the DBA according to the provisions of German tax law be taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is no time limit - contrary to the comparable regulation of the double taxation agreement in Switzerland"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A tax levied in Italy on this income is to be offset against German tax in accordance with the provisions of German tax law on the offsetting of foreign taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the credit does not take place insofar as the German tax could be levied according to the general rules of the DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The income tax levied in the Italian Republic does not represent low taxation for the application of Section 2 AStG within the meaning of Section 2 (2) No. 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, this does not apply to persons who are only taxed on income from Italian sources"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "21 Personal requirements211 One of the personal requirements for the extended limited tax liability is that the taxpayer was subject to unlimited income tax as a German for at least five years in the last ten years before the end of his unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The unrestricted tax liability according to \u00a7 1 paragraph 1 sentence 1 EStG is equivalent to the unlimited tax liability according to \u00a7 1 paragraph 1 of the income tax law of the former German Democratic Republic"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the unlimited tax liability ended before January 1, 1991, the application of Sections 2 to 5 AStG remains unaffected (Section 21 (6) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The deadlines are according to \u00a7 108 Abs 1 AO i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7\u00a7 187 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "BGB to calculate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In detail, the following should be noted: If the taxpayer was subject to unlimited tax liability in Germany several times during the relevant ten-year period, the periods in which there was unlimited tax liability must be added together"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Domestic stays that did not give rise to unlimited tax liability (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "because they did not last longer than six months, because they were for visiting, recreation, spa or similar private purposes or because the taxpayer enjoyed diplomatic or other privileges under international law) are not to be counted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, short-term interruptions to a stay in Germany are not deducted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "German is anyone who has German citizenship or is one of the refugees, displaced persons and their relatives named in Article 116 (1) of the Basic Law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The extended limited tax liability is not excluded by the fact that the taxpayer was also a national of another country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant that he gave up his German citizenship after having been subject to unlimited taxation as a German for five years during the relevant ten-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a taxpayer moves his domicile several times from Germany to another country and from there back to Germany, each time the unlimited tax liability ends, it must be checked whether the personal requirements of the extended limited tax liability are met according to the circumstances relevant for this change of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "212 The limited tax liability applies to the individual"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, spouses are to be assessed individually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It must be determined for each of them separately whether the conditions for the extended limited tax liability are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Each spouse is entitled to the exemptions or exemption limits of \u00a7\u00a7 2 to 4 AStG; if one spouse does not exhaust them, they cannot be transferred to the other"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "22 Low taxation221 The extended limited tax liability presupposes that the taxpayer is only resident in low-tax foreign areas or is not resident in any area (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "because he constantly changes his stay)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer is resident in those areas in which he is taxable under local law due to his place of residence, habitual residence or another similar feature"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer does not show, in accordance with Section 90 (2), that he is taxable in an area in this way, it must be assumed that he is not resident in any area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "222 A foreign territory is taxed at a low rate if one of the two conditions described below is met: The foreign territory levies an income tax on an unmarried person with an income of DM 150,000 that is more than a third lower than the German income tax (see Section 2 Paragraph 2 No. 1 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "As of 1994, this applies to a foreign tax rate of less than 2517 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the tax burden comparison, the amount of 150,000 DM has to be converted into the relevant foreign currency according to the rate at the beginning of the year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "At the request of the taxpayer, the annual average exchange rate can also be used as a basis for the conversion if he can prove that this is more favorable for him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The income tax levied in the foreign territory must take into account the income taxes levied by the foreign state or its political subdivisions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The German income tax does not include the solidarity surcharge (see the BFH judgment of 30 November 1988 on the supplementary tax, BStBl 1989 II, 365)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the foreign territory, the taxpayer can be granted substantial preferential taxation (see Section 2 (2) No. 2 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "given if people moving from abroad are exempt from income tax; tax breaks (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxation on the basis of their consumption, favorable tax contracts, enactments or tax deferrals without consideration of the taxable ability) can be obtained; the income from the economic interests remaining in the country are taxed preferentially over other income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient if the items listed in nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 are granted for a substantial part of the income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is also preferential taxation if the foreign state in which the natural person is resident grants preferential taxation to general taxation according to its legal system, without it being important that the respective person concerned is actually granted this preferential taxation or by law can be granted because of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to the tax law of a foreign state, income from abroad is not subject to taxation for all persons resident in its territory (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Territoriality principle), no preferential taxation is to be seen here compared to general taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if income comes from abroad in general, without any further requirements related to residence (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in Great Britain), are only taxed if they are transferred to the country of residence (taxation on the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Remittance basis)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Regardless of this, a preferential taxation compared to general taxation cannot be ruled out in these countries either"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In individual cases, the tax authorities can request the submission of tax returns, foreign tax assessments or comparable evidence (see Section 90 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "223 If there are still doubts as to whether an area with low taxation within the meaning of Section 2 (2) No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 AStG, the Federal Office of Finance makes the necessary determinations upon request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "224 Even if the requirements of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "222 excludes low taxation if the taxpayer can prove that the total tax payable on income under German limited tax liability is at least two thirds of the income tax that the taxpayer would have to pay in the case of unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The following should be noted: The taxes to be paid on total income in the case of German limited tax liability include both the income taxes that are payable in the Federal Republic of Germany and the income taxes that are payable in the country of residence or third countries (actual taxation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also includes the Swiss church tax based on income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When determining the total (German and foreign) income tax that would have to be paid in the case of unlimited tax liability, fictitious tax calculations must be carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If, when determining German income tax, provisions of domestic German tax law are expressly linked to the domestic situation (spouse splitting, child allowance, household allowance, care allowance), then for the purposes of determining the income tax to be paid with unlimited tax liability, the facts must be assumed that would exist with unlimited tax liability of the taxpayer (debit taxation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The assessment options for spouses according to \u00a7\u00a7 26 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "EStG remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of spouses, it is therefore a prerequisite that they do not live permanently apart"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If, according to this, \u00a7 32a (5) EStG is to be applied in the case of unlimited tax liability, the German income tax resulting therefrom must be divided according to the ratio of the income of the taxpayer to the income resulting from the inclusion of the income of the spouse for the purpose of the comparative calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The German tax is to be set at the amount that results from the application of the DBA or \u00a7 34c EStG (see BFH judgment of 26 November 1986 BStBl 1987 II, 363)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The German income tax is not to be reduced by the creditable corporation tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When determining the foreign tax, reference is not made to the foreign tax actually paid, but to the foreign tax that would have been incurred if the taxpayers had the same income if they were not subject to limited but unlimited taxation, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "his place of residence or habitual abode in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In individual cases, the fictitious determination of this foreign tax can cause difficulties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the taxpayer must provide the relevant proof of foreign taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "He therefore has to bear the disadvantage if the foreign taxation cannot be determined due to foreign law (see BFH judgment of 26 November 1986 BStBl 1987 II, 363)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The official exchange rate at the end of the assessment period is decisive for the conversion of foreign tax amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "To simplify matters, the under nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2 and 3, the fictitious determination of the foreign tax can be dispensed with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer agrees to such a simplification or is not able to provide evidence of fictitious foreign taxation (see no.3 above), the German tax must be applied, which would have to be paid for all domestic and foreign income with unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is based on the German tax before crediting foreign taxes and before taking into account tax exemptions due to double taxation agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "225 If, as in the case of Switzerland, the tax collection period (tax period) and tax assessment period differ from one another, the following applies: The extended limited taxable income must be compared with the taxes on which this income served as the assessment basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For further details, reference is made to Section II No. 3 of the BMF letter dated May 23, 1990 - IV C 5 - S-1351 - 4/80 - (BStBl 1980 I, 282) on the calculation of the tax burden for interim income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "23 Major domestic economic interests231 Whether there are significant domestic economic interests within the meaning of Section 2 (3) AStG is to be assessed according to German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In particular, when examining whether the income limit of Section 2 (3) No. 2 AStG has been exceeded, the principles of German tax law on the determination of income must be applied; the asset limit of Section 2 (3) No. 3 AStG is exceeded, the provisions of the Valuation Act must be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income and assets for which the German tax laws (except DTA) provide for an exemption are not recognized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "232 In principle, domestic interests include all those listed in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2502 and No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "312 listed income and assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, dividends, interest and license fees that are paid by domestic debtors, even if they flow to a foreign permanent establishment, must also be recognized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income from self-employed and non-self-employed work is not to be included if the work is carried out abroad and is only or has only been used in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "24 Indirect domestic interests241 When examining whether there are significant economic interests in the person of the person moving away, according to Section 2 (4) AStG, income and assets of an intermediary company within the meaning of Section 5 AStG must also be included in accordance with his participation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to the allocation according to Section 5 AStG, Section 2 (4) AStG is not just low-taxed passive income within the meaning of Section 8 AStG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "503)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "242 The law for income and assets of a family foundation according to Section 15 AStG does not provide for a comparable regulation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "25 Extent of the extended limited income taxation250 General2501 The extended limited income tax liability extends beyond the income specified in Section 49 EStG to all other income that is not foreign income according to Section 34d EStG (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "extended domestic income)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Unless already covered by Section 49 (1) EStG, this is income from commercial operations that a) are not attributable to a domestic or foreign permanent establishment or b) are earned from surety and surety commissions, the debtor of which is fully taxable; Income from the sale of assets that are part of the fixed assets of a foreign company and are located in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also includes a profit not already falling under \u00a7 17 EStG from the sale of shares in a corporation that has its management or its registered office in Germany; Income from capital assets within the meaning of \u00a7 20 EStG, if the debtor is fully taxable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This includes e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Interest paid by residents on borrower's note loans to extended restricted taxpayers; Income from the rental and leasing of movable property in Germany, provided that this is not part of a material item located abroad; Income from recurring payments within the meaning of Section 22 No. 1 EStG, if the person liable is subject to unlimited taxation or is domiciled in Germany; Income from speculative transactions within the meaning of Section 22 No. 2 EStG, if the assets sold are not located abroad; Income from services if the person obliged to pay for the service is fully taxable or has his seat in Germany; other income that German tax law (\u00a7\u00a7 34d, 49 EStG) does not attribute to either Germany or abroad (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income from movable property that is not part of the fixed assets of a foreign company); Income that the taxpayer according to \u00a7 5 AStG or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 15 AStG are attributable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2502 Including the income already recorded under Section 49 (1) EStG, the following are subject to the extended limited tax liability: Income from agriculture and forestry (Sections 13 to 14 EStG), insofar as this is not operated abroad; Income from commercial operations (\u00a7\u00a7 15 to 17 EStG), which are achieved a) by a permanent establishment maintained in Germany or a permanent representative appointed in Germany; b) through the operation of own or chartered ships by aircraft for transports between domestic ports or from domestic to foreign ports (including domestic transport services associated with such transports); c) from transports and transport services according to letter b by a company within the framework of an international operating group or a pool agreement in which a company with its registered office or management in Germany performs the transport; d) through artistic, sporting, artistic or similar performances in Germany or through their exploitation in Germany, including income from other services related to these services, regardless of who receives the income, insofar as the aforementioned services are not included in the income within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "3 and 4 belong; e) through the income generated under the requirements of Section 17 EStG from the sale of a share in a corporation (Section 17 EStG) that has its registered office or management in Germany; f) through the sale of immovable property, material items or rights within the meaning of No. 6 insofar as they do not belong to the income within the meaning of letter a; g) in the in No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2501 nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 named way; Income from self-employed work (Section 18 EStG) that is or has been exercised or used in Germany; Income from non-self-employed work (Section 19 EStG) that is or has been exercised or used in Germany and income that is granted from domestic public coffers, including the coffers of the Deutsche Bundesbahn and the Deutsche Bundesbank, with regard to a current or previous employment relationship; Income from capital assets (\u00a7 20 EStG), if a) the debtor is fully taxable or b) the capital assets from domestic property, domestic rights that are subject to the provisions of civil law on land, or ships that are registered in a domestic ship register are secured directly or indirectly; Income from renting and leasing (\u00a7 21 EStG) a) from immovable property if it is located in Germany or is entered in a domestic public book or register or is realized in a domestic permanent establishment or otherwise used in Switzerland; b) of movable property in Switzerland, unless it is part of a material item located abroad; other income within the meaning of \u00a7 22 EStG, if a) in the case of recurring payments, the person obliged to provide services is subject to unlimited taxation; b) in speculative transactions within the meaning of Section 23 of the Income Tax Act, the assets sold are not located abroad or consist of a participation in a domestic corporation; c) In the case of income from services, the party obliged to pay for the service is subject to unlimited taxation; the under no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2501 nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8 and 9 mentioned income; those under nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5 to 8, even if they belong to a foreign company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "251 Determination of the taxable income 2511 Income that is covered by Section 2 AStG beyond Section 1 (4) EStG is also to be determined according to German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Operating expenses and business expenses may only be deducted if they are economically related to this income (see Section 50 (1) EStG and BFH judgment of March 28, 1984 BStBl II, 620)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2512 Negative income within the meaning of Section 49 (1) EStG can be offset both with positive income within the meaning of Section 49 (1) EStG and with positive extended limited taxable income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Negative extended limited taxable income can be offset with positive extended limited taxable income as well as positive income within the meaning of Section 49 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A loss deduction (Section 10d EStG) is permissible both against positive, extended limited taxable income and against income within the meaning of Section 49 (1) EStG, provided that the requirements of Section 50 (1) sentence 3 EStG are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prohibition of loss compensation in accordance with Section 50 (2) EStG therefore neither applies to income that is subject to tax deduction, nor to income within the meaning of Section 20 (1) nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5 and 7 EStG (BFH decision of 3 November 1982 BStBl 1983 II, 259 bstbl-1983-ii-0259)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If losses are taken into account, the minimum tax according to Section 2 (5) sentence 3 AStG must not be undercut"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, this does not rule out that the extended limited tax liability results in a lower tax than the limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2513 The provisions on limited tax liability also apply to tax exemptions and other deductions (Section 50 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Spouses are assessed individually (Section 25 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "252 Income to be included in the assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2522 Income that has been subject to tax deduction from wages must not be included in the assessment; However, they must be taken into account when determining the applicable tax rate (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "253)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 39d EStG remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the employee with extended limited tax liability is a \"cross-border commuter\", Section 50 (4) and (5) EStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "253 Calculation of the tax and application of the progression reservation 2531 Paragraph 2 (5) AStG extends the limited tax liability in such a way that, in addition to the income subject to the extended restricted tax liability, all foreign income of the taxpayer must also be included in the determination of the tax rate (progression reservation; see example for Effect with DBA in point"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2021 No. 3)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2532 The foreign income to be taken into account must be determined in accordance with German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Special expenses - with the exception of donations within the meaning of \u00a7 10b EStG -, deductions due to extraordinary burdens as well as benefits that are only granted with unlimited tax liability (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Exemption under the DBA), are not taken into account when determining the applicable tax rate - subject to the cross-border commuter regulation of Section 50 (4) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When determining the amount of income and the German tax, which are decisive for calculating the tax rate, foreign taxes may only be taken into account within the framework of Section 50 (6) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2533 Income tax is to be determined in accordance with Section 32a (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Subject to Section 50 (3) sentence 3 EStG, a special tax allowance of DM 864 must be deducted from income and the income tax is at least 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "of extended limited taxable income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The income tax is subject to the following in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2521 to be credited with the tax deductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, since the total amount of tax withheld must not be undercut, a reimbursement is not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2534 For the crediting of corporation tax, reference is made to R 213h EStR 1993"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "254 Procedural issues 2541 Extended restricted taxpayers must submit a tax return on all income received in the past calendar year to the local tax office according to Section 56 (2) sentence 2 EStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "At the request of the tax office, the taxpayer must also name an authorized recipient if he wants to exclude the fictitious access of \u00a7 123 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2542 When changing from unrestricted to extended limited tax liability in the course of an assessment period or vice versa, two assessments must be carried out (see R 227 EStR 1993 on limited tax liability)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If it is a case of Section 50 (4) EStG (cross-border commuters) and the applicant is only liable for unlimited tax in part of the calendar year, he / she is considered to be subject to unlimited tax for the entire calendar year (reference to Section 50 (4) sentence 8 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "26 Limitation to the tax in the case of unlimited tax liability 261 According to \u00a7 2 (6) AStG, the total tax to be paid due to the extended limited tax liability is to be limited if the taxpayer provides evidence that it does not include the German tax to be paid under the assumption of unlimited tax liability and exclusively domestic residence exceeds"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "With limited tax liability (d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the tax incurred without application of \u00a7 2 AStG) may not be undercut"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "262 When calculating the comparative amounts, the following should be noted: a) The tax to be paid in the case of unlimited tax liability is the tax liability that would result if the total world income were used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The tax reductions under Section 34c EStG and the DBA as well as special expenses, extraordinary burdens and tax exemptions that would have to be deducted or granted in the case of sole residence in Germany must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of spouses, this means that the splitting table must be used if the spouses live together abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The assessment options for spouses in \u00a7\u00a7 26 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "EStG remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The tax resulting from joint assessment must be divided in proportion to the income attributable to the respective spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "b) The tax to be paid in the case of limited tax liability is basically the tax to be assessed without the application of Section 2 AStG plus German wage tax as well as the German tax deduction from capital gains and the tax deduction within the meaning of Section 50a EStG, unless Section 50 (4) and 5 sentence 3 EStG applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "263 If \u200b\u200bthe extended limited tax liability only existed for part of the year, the comparative calculations must also be based on this part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of spouses, the comparison calculations are to be made separately for each person (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "212)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "3 Wealth tax 30 Extended limited wealth tax liability A taxpayer to whom Section 2 AStG applies is subject to extended limited wealth tax liability up to ten years after the end of the year in which the unlimited income tax liability ended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the prerequisites of \u00a7 2 AStG cease to apply during an assessment period, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "because the taxpayer has moved to a non-taxing country or has given up his essential domestic interests, this does not affect the determination made for the previous reference date"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: An unrestricted taxpayer with substantial domestic interests moves to a low-tax area on June 1, 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The extended limited wealth tax liability exists until the end of the year 2000 d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "for the first time on January 1, 1991, and for the last time on January 1, 2000.If the taxpayer moves to a non-taxable area on January 1, 1995 or at a later point in time in 1995, the extended limited wealth tax liability ceases to apply with effect from January 1, 1996 extended limited tax liability 311 \u00a7 3 AStG extends the extended limited wealth tax liability to assets whose income is subject to the extended limited income tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "312 The extended limited wealth tax liability accordingly extends beyond the domestic assets named in section 121 (2) BewG also to the domestic assets not listed there of the extended limited wealth taxpayer (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "expanded domestic assets)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, domestic assets include: capital claims against domestic debtors (Section 110 (1) No. 1 BewG); Savings deposits and bank balances at financial institutions in Germany as well as domestic and foreign means of payment located in Germany (Section 110 (1) No. 2 BewG); Shares and shares in corporations, investment funds and open real estate funds as well as credit balances in cooperatives in Germany (Section 110 (1) No. 3 BewG); Claims to pensions and other recurring payments against debtors in Germany as well as usufruct and rights of use to assets in Germany (Section 110 (1) No. 4 BewG); Inventions and copyrights that are exploited domestically (Section 110 (1) No. 5 BewG); Insurance claims against insurance companies in Germany (Section 110 Paragraph 1 No. 6 BewG); the excess of circulating operating resources of an agricultural and forestry company in Germany (Section 110 (1) No. 7 BewG); Assets that are intended to serve an agricultural and forestry company in Germany or a commercial operation in Germany, but do not actually serve such a company of the taxpayer at the point in time relevant for the assessment of wealth tax, as well as mineral resources if they are deducted for asset reduction to be carried out when determining income (Section 110 (1) No. 8 BewG); Economic goods in furnished apartments in Germany that belong to non-business owners and are permanently rented together with the living space (Section 110 (1) No. 9 BewG); Economic goods listed in Section 110 Paragraph 1 Nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10 to 12 BewG, if the income from this for a person who is fully taxable would not be foreign income within the meaning of Section 34d EStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2501); Assets whose income is subject to extended limited tax liability according to Section 5 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2501 No. 9); Assets that are attributable to the extended limited taxpayer according to \u00a7 15 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "155)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "32 Determination of the extended domestic assets 321 The tax exemptions, exemption limits and tax exemptions applicable according to Sections 110 and 111 BewG must also be taken into account when determining the extended domestic assets (Section 3 (1) AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 121 (3) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "322 Assets that are tax-exempt under the Wealth Tax Act or other laws are also excluded from the calculation of the extended domestic assets (Section 3 (1) AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 114 and Section 121 (3) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to assets that are exempt from German taxation under a DTA, unless the agreement expressly allows the application of \u00a7 3 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "323 When determining the expanded domestic assets, a deduction of debts and encumbrances is only possible to the extent that these are economically related to the expanded domestic assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Because of the economic context, see Section 42 VStR 1993 324. Of the extended domestic assets, an amount of no more than DM 60,000 remains tax-free (tax exemption according to Section 3 (2) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the exemption cannot be used or not fully used, there is no possibility of transferring it to the domestic assets according to Section 121 (2) BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "325 If negative extended domestic assets result from the deduction of debts and encumbrances even before the exemption according to Section 3 (2) AStG has been taken into account, this can be offset against the positive domestic assets (Section 121 (2) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the opposite case, negative domestic assets (Section 121 (2) BewG) can be offset against positive, expanded domestic assets after deduction of the tax exemption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "326 spouses who are subject to limited tax liability are not assessed together (Section 14 (1) VStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, the extended domestic assets must also be determined and recorded separately for each spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The relevant allowances, exemption limits, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "are available to each spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Unused allowances and allowances cannot be transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "327 For persons with limited tax liability, a tax limit of DM 20,000 generally applies (Section 8 (2) VStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the extended domestic assets remaining after deduction of the exemption of a maximum of DM 60,000 together with the other domestic assets (Section 121 (2) BewG) do not reach the amount of DM 20,000, they remain tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "33 Assessment The transition from the unrestricted to the extended restricted wealth tax liability or vice versa is just as much a reason for a subsequent assessment as the transition from the unrestricted to the limited wealth tax liability or vice versa (Section 17 (1) VStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a person who has previously been subject to unlimited wealth tax or a person not subject to wealth tax is subject to the extended limited wealth tax liability for the first time on a certain key date, a subsequent assessment must therefore be carried out, unless a main assessment is already to be carried out on this key date"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The transition from the limited to the extended limited wealth tax liability or vice versa can be the reason for a new assessment (Section 16 (1) No. 1 VStG; from January 1, 1995: Section 16 (1) No. 2 VStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When examining the new assessment limits, the taxable assets according to \u00a7 3 Paragraph 1 AStG, reduced by the tax exemption according to \u00a7 3 Paragraph 2 AStG, must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: If a person subject to limited wealth tax had domestic assets of DM 300,000 on January 1, 1995 and assets of DM 170,000 are added on January 1, 1996, which are subject to the extended limited wealth tax liability, the wealth tax is more than DM 1,000 compared to the last wealth tax assessment ( 170000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "60,000 DM = 110,000 DM, thereof 1%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "= 1100 DM)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A new assessment is made on January 1, 1996 4 Inheritance and gift tax40 Extended restricted inheritance and gift tax The extended limited tax liability according to \u00a7 4 AStG occurs if the tax liability is subject to the deceased's unlimited income tax liability up to ten years after the end of the year or Schenkers ended, arose and the requirements of Section 2 (1) sentence 1 AStG were met at the time the tax liability arose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted here that Section 2 (1) No. 1 (b) of the ErbStG 1974 extended the unlimited inheritance tax liability to German citizens if they had not been abroad for more than five years at the time the donation was made, without being in To have a domicile in Germany (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "extended unrestricted tax liability)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "An extended, limited inheritance tax liability can therefore only occur when the period in which the extended, unrestricted inheritance tax liability can occur has expired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "41 Extent of the extended, restricted inheritance and gift tax liability411 The extended, restricted inheritance and gift tax liability extends over the provisions set out in Section 2 (1) No. 3 ErbStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the domestic assets referred to in Section 121 (2) BewG: capital claims against domestic debtors; savings deposits and bank balances at domestic financial institutions; shares and shares in corporations, investment funds and open real estate funds as well as credit balances in domestic cooperatives; claims to pensions and other recurring payments against debtors domestically as well as usufruct and usage rights to assets domestically; inventions and copyrights that are exploited domestically; insurance claims against insurance companies domestically; movable assets that are located in Germany; assets whose income is subject to the extended limited tax liability according to \u00a7 5 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2501 No. 9); assets that are to be assigned to the extended limited taxpayer according to \u00a7 15 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "155)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "412 When determining the acquisitions subject to the extended restricted tax liability, a deduction of debts and encumbrances is only possible insofar as these are economically related to these acquisitions (see Section 10 (6) ErbStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the consideration of negative assets, the remarks on No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "325 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "413 The tax exemption of DM 2000 provided for limited tax liability (cf. Section 16 (2) ErbStG) is also granted if there is only inheritance tax liability under Section 4 (1) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "42 Minimum taxation421 The extended restricted inheritance or gift tax liability does not apply if the taxpayer provides evidence that a tax equivalent to German inheritance tax is to be paid abroad on the assets that are additionally taxed according to \u00a7 4 AStG, which is at least 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the German inheritance tax applicable to this property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It then remains with the limited tax liability according to \u00a7 2 Abs 1 Nr 3 ErbStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If there is no tax liability for the testator or donor according to \u00a7 2 AStG, \u00a7 4 paragraph 2 AStG is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the German tax, \u00a7 14 ErbStG applies accordingly to previous acquisitions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "422 When calculating the comparison, all foreign taxes that correspond to German inheritance and gift taxes must be taken into account, even if they are in countries other than the foreign country of residence of the testator or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Schenkers are to be paid (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "also local taxes from cantons and communes)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxes payable on the part of the acquisition that is also taxable in accordance with Section 4 AStG in Germany and abroad are to be determined in accordance with Section 21 (1) sentence 2 ErbStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5 Intermediate companies50 General501 Section 5 AStG supplements Sections 2 to 4 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provision prevents the extended limited tax liability from being circumvented by involving a foreign company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "502 Paragraph 5 (1) of the AStG defines the group of people for whom the allocation of income and assets is possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, as in \u00a7\u00a7 3 and 4 AStG, the focus is not on persons within the meaning of \u00a7 2 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 AStG, but only on persons who fall under \u00a7 2 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 No. 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is therefore irrelevant whether these persons have significant economic interests in Germany (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "503 The in point"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "502 must hold a stake in a foreign company within the meaning of Section 7 AStG alone or together with persons with unlimited tax liability (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If this requirement is met, the income that falls under \u00a7\u00a7 8 and 14 AStG (low taxed passive income) and is not foreign income within the meaning of \u00a7 34d EStG is allocated proportionally to these persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The amount of income is to be determined in accordance with the provisions of German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 5 (1) sentence 2 AStG, the extended restricted tax liability is also extended to the assets of the foreign company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "51 Allocation of Income and Assets511 Income Tax5111 If a person within the meaning of Section 2 AStG has a stake in a foreign company within the meaning of Section 7 AStG, the income generated by the intermediary company, which is specified under No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2502 and at the same time interim income is to be assigned in such a way that it is treated as actually obtained by the intermediary company, but the resulting tax consequences apply to the person within the meaning of \u00a7 2 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Negative income is also included in accordance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2512 must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5112 The income generated by the company is viewed and attributed to the person within the meaning of Section 2 AStG as having accrued to the company in the last logical second of the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5113 A German tax withheld or assessed and paid on the income of the company is offset against the income tax payable in accordance with Sections 2 and 5 AStG in accordance with Section 36 (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "512 Wealth tax and inheritance tax 5121 Assets or parts of assets on the basis of which income is attributable to the taxpayer according to \u00a7 5 AStG are subject to the extended limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The assets allocated in this way are to be treated as business assets in accordance with the regulation of \u00a7 97 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the company's assets fall under Section 121 (2) BewG as well as expanded domestic assets, they are to be added to the person's expanded domestic assets in accordance with their participation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A German wealth tax assessed and paid on the company's assets will be offset against the wealth tax to be paid in accordance with Sections 3 and 5 of the AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5122 For the extended restricted inheritance tax liability, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5121 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "52 Liability of the attributed assets The assets on which the income attributable to a person according to Section 5 (1) AStG is based are only liable for the income tax owed by this person for this income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "53 Procedure The income and assets that are attributable to the extended limited taxpayer are separately in accordance with \u00a7 18 AStG, if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "also uniformly (if several emigrants are involved in the intermediary society), to be determined (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18111)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6 Treatment of significant holdings in the event of a change of residence abroad60 Tax liability601 According to \u00a7 6 AStG, unrestricted taxpayers have the capital growth of significant holdings in domestic corporations in accordance with the principles of \u00a7 17 when they transfer to the limited tax liability or with the fulfillment of certain other circumstances (\u00a7 6 (3) AStG) EStG to be taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Can the hidden reserves already be taxed according to other provisions (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 21 UmwStG), they take precedence over \u00a7 6 AStG (see BFH judgment of February 28, 1990 BStBl II, 615)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "602 Establishing a second residence abroad with the continued unrestricted tax liability triggers the taxation of capital gains only in the cases of Section 6 (3) No. 2 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "61 Personal and material requirements611 Personal requirements6111 The application of \u00a7 6 AStG requires that the unlimited tax liability has existed for at least ten years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that the person also has German citizenship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6112 Was the taxpayer or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "his legal predecessor (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "62) resident several times in Germany, the periods of time during which there was unlimited tax liability must be added up"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Periods of unlimited tax liability that ended before June 21, 1948 are not to be taken into account for reasons of equity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "612 Factual requirements 6121 The exit taxation within the meaning of Section 6 AStG extends to shares in domestic corporations for which the requirements of Section 17 (1) EStG - with the exception of the sale - are met at the time the unlimited tax liability ends"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is then necessary that the taxpayer in a domestic company within the last five years before moving abroad significantly, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to more than 25 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": ", was directly or indirectly involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For this, it is sufficient if this participation only increases to more than 25% for a short period within the five-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "has passed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "At the time of moving away, shares of 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "or less trigger a taxation according to \u00a7 6 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6122 If the person moving away acquired the shares free of charge during the five-year period, it is sufficient if the minimum participation was met in the person of the legal predecessor or one of the legal predecessors"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "613 Taxation of capital growth 6131 The capital growth taxable according to \u00a7 6 AStG is subject to unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is to be invested together with other income accrued to the taxpayer in the relevant assessment period up to the date of the end of the unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "R 227 EStR 1993 must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6132 When determining income, the provisions of Section 17 EStG and Section 53 EStDV on the determination of acquisition costs as well as Section 9 BewG on the determination of a common value are to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The tax rate for the increase in assets is measured according to \u00a7 34 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6133 \u00a7 6 AStG only applies to cases in which the average value of the shares on the move exceeds the acquisition costs; the provision does not lead to the realization of losses (see BFH judgment of 28 February 1990 BStBl II, 615)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "614 Disposal of shares after the change of residence 6141 If a share is sold after the change of residence, the resulting capital gain is subject to \u00a7 49 Paragraph 1 No. 2 Letter e i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 17 EStG of limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The increase in value before moving abroad must also be included in the taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "With the assessment, the capital gain is to be reduced by the already taxed asset growth"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: The taxpayer moved to Germany on January 1, 1977 and moved away on December 31, 1988"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A substantial investment in a domestic company which the taxpayer acquired on January 1, 1975 for 1 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Had acquired DM, had on January 1, 1977 a fair value of 3 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM and on December 31, 1988 of 10 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It will be sold on January 1, 1991 for 17 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM sold"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the assessment period 1988, the taxpayer is responsible for the increase in value since the move of 7 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM (= 10 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "3 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM) subject to unlimited tax liability (\u00a7 6 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "17 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the 1991 assessment period, the entire capital gain of 16 million is subject to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM (17 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM) less the already taxed 7 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM (Section 6 (1) last sentence AStG), a total of 9 million"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "DM, the limited tax liability (\u00a7 49 Paragraph 1 No. 2 e EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6142 In the event of a later actual sale, a loss can result even if a profit is achieved by reducing the already taxed increase in assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the sale actually led to a loss and if the increase in assets was positive when moving away, this loss from the actual sale must be increased by the positive increase in assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the increase in assets was negative when moving away, but the actual sale led to a positive result, the original acquisition costs must be used as the basis for calculating the profit from the sale (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6133)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6143 Section 6 (4) and (5) AStG does not apply to the sale of shares"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6144 If the taxpayer has become fully taxable again and if he then sells the substantial investment, then no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6141 and 6142 apply with the proviso that the unrestricted tax liability takes the place of the restricted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a correction was made in accordance with Section 6 (4) AStG when the unrestricted tax liability was re-established, the reduction in the capital gain in accordance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6141615 Effect of double taxation agreements 6151 The taxation of capital growth according to \u00a7 6 AStG is not excluded by the fact that the taxpayer becomes resident for tax purposes in a country with which a double taxation agreement exists and the profit from the later actual sale of the share according to the agreement in the Federal Republic of Germany could not be taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "6152 The taxation of the profit from the actual sale of the share does not apply if the taxpayer was resident at the time of the sale in a country with which a double taxation agreement exists that only assigns the right to tax this profit to this country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, due to the taxation of the profit from the actual sale in the country of residence, the profit already taxed according to Section 6 (1) AStG may be taxed a second time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This can be avoided if the country of residence), when determining the capital gain, ties in or with the value ratios when moving away"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "exempts the capital gain in this respect or b) offsets the tax levied under Section 6 (1) AStG on its tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is expressly provided for in some DTAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Value link for DBA Switzerland, DBA Italy and tax credit for DBA Sweden, DBA Canada)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In addition, a mutual agreement procedure can be initiated with the aim of avoiding double taxation that is not eliminated by a DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "62 Free legal transaction 621 If a taxpayer has shares through a wholly or partially free legal transaction (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "acquired by gift, inheritance contract, testamentary disposition and legacy), the period during which his legal predecessor was subject to unlimited tax liability must be taken into account in accordance with Section 6 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "622 If the shares have been transferred several times in succession in the manner specified in Section 6 (2) sentence 1 AStG (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in cases of so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Chain gifts), the entire duration of the unlimited tax liability of each legal predecessor is included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Periods in which the acquirer of the shares or one or more legal predecessors were simultaneously unrestrictedly liable for tax are only recognized once in accordance with Section 6 (2) sentence 3 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a majority of people jointly own the shares, the respective periods are also only to be set once"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "63 Facts equivalent to change of residence Legal transaction between living persons for persons who are not subject to unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The recipients of the units must therefore be limited or non-taxable persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It can also be a domestic or foreign partnership as long as it does not involve unlimited taxpayers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The establishment of a place of residence or habitual abode or the fulfillment of a similar characteristic in a foreign country, if the taxpayer is thereby considered to be resident in this country under a DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This affects the cases in which a natural person z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "maintains a domestic place of residence and thus remains fully taxable, but is deemed to be resident in the other contracting state for the purposes of the agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the Federal Republic of Germany retains the right to tax from the sale of shares under the DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The contribution of the shares in a domestic corporation to a foreign company or a foreign permanent establishment of the person with unlimited tax liability if the German tax law for a possible capital gain is excluded under a DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the foreign company or permanent establishment already exists or is only established at the time of the contribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In each individual case, it must be checked whether the German tax law for a profit from the sale of the shares after their contribution to foreign business assets is excluded according to the relevant double taxation agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The exchange of shares in a domestic corporation for shares in a foreign corporation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A cross-border exchange of shares in a member state of the EU does not lead to a profit realization under the conditions of the conversion tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of double taxation agreements, the taxation of the increase in assets according to \u00a7 6 Paragraph 1 No. 4 AStG intervenes regardless of whether the German tax law is restricted or not in the event of a later sale of the received shares under a double tax agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the taxable person deposits the shares in a domestic corporation against the granting of shares in a foreign company, whose income is with the taxpayer subject to additional taxation according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "AStG, the transferred shares are to be recognized in the add-on balance sheet of the foreign company at the mean value taken into account in accordance with Section 6 (1) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "64 Temporary absence641 If you return within five years, you can only accept a temporary absence if the intention to return already existed at the time of departure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is to be assessed according to the overall circumstances of the individual case; mere declarations of intent are not enough"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "642 In the event of a temporary absence, the tax liability that arises in accordance with Section 6 (1) to (3) AStG is finally or provisionally determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Upon return, a final decision according to \u00a7 175 Paragraph 1 No. 2 AO must be revoked, a provisional decision according to \u00a7 165 Paragraph 2 AO must be changed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "65 Forbearance651 The provision of Section 6 (5) AStG represents a special deferral regulation for the income tax owed from the taxation of capital gains within the meaning of Section 6 AStG; in this respect, the general deferral regulation of \u00a7 222 AO is extended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a deferral in accordance with Section 6 (5) AStG, interest may also be charged in accordance with Section 234 (1) AO (BFH judgment of October 16, 1991 BStBl 1992 II, 321)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "652 In cases of an only temporary absence within the meaning of Section 6 (4) AStG, a deferral must be issued for the duration of this absence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In individual cases, this can mean a deferral of less than five years if an early return of the person concerned is to be expected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Conversely, the deferral period can in individual cases also apply to more than five years if the period of temporary absence according to Section 6 (4) second half-sentence AStG has been extended, but no more than ten years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "7 Participation in foreign intermediate companies70 Additional taxation701 Sections 7 to 14 AStG (additional taxation) extend the tax liability of unrestricted taxpayers to income that accrues through passive acquisition of foreign companies and is subject to low taxation (interim income)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "702 In relation to other provisions, the following must be observed: Sections 7 to 14 AStG do not affect the unrestricted tax liability of foreign companies in Germany (cf. BFH judgment of 23 June 1992 BStBl II, 972); the additional taxation then does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The additional taxation does not extend to income that is to be recorded by the taxpayer as a result of other regulations (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7\u00a7 39 or 41 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 42 AO takes precedence over \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG, insofar as the abuse results from general characteristics"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This presupposes, however, that the chosen design, even when assessed against the legal purpose of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG, still presents itself as an abuse of design options of the law (BFH judgment of 23 October 1991 BStBl 1992 II, 1026)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In order to be able to apply \u00a7 42 AO, additional circumstances must therefore arise that characterize the design as manipulation, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the lack of an independent economic function of foreign companies that are only formally involved in generating income (in particular letterbox companies)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The mere generation of income from passive acquisition, on the other hand, in itself only triggers additional taxation, but does not justify an allegation of abuse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "As a result, \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG contain within their regulatory area a special regulation that precedes \u00a7 42 AO (see BFH judgments of 23 October 1991 BStBl 1992 II, 1026, and of 10 June 1992 BStBl II, 1029)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 42 AO is applicable if Sections 7 to 14 AStG are circumvented through the abuse of structuring options under the law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "703 The share in a foreign intermediate company is subject to wealth tax in accordance with the wealth tax regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "704 Sections 7 to 14 AStG do not affect the limited tax liability of the foreign intermediate company with regard to its domestic income and domestic assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to \u00a7 12 AStG, the German tax levied afterwards is offset against the German taxes from the additional amount (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1212)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "705 transactions of other persons with an intermediate company (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the sale of a patent by a resident to a closely related intermediate company) are to be assessed according to the general regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "71 Tax liability of domestic shareholders711 Taxpayers are subject to unrestricted taxpayers who directly own a share in the nominal capital of a foreign company or (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "due to \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 and 42 AO) is to be attributed for tax purposes (domestic participants)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This requirement must exist at the end of the relevant financial year of the foreign company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "712 Are unlimited taxpayers indirectly in a foreign company, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "participates through another foreign company (Section 7 (2) sentence 2 AStG), the interim income accruing in the first-mentioned company is allocated to the other company in accordance with Section 14 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "141) and are therefore subject to additional taxation for those with unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This presupposes that the holdings in both foreign companies meet the requirements of Section 7 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "72 Minimum shareholding721 To determine whether the minimum shareholding within the meaning of Section 7 (2) AStG is given, the following must be stated: Shares (voting rights) that are directly owned or owned by unrestricted taxpayers (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "due to \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 and 42 AO) are taxable; This also includes shares in a) corporations, associations of persons and assets that are personally exempt from corporation tax in accordance with Section 5 KStG; b) persons who are also fully taxable in another country under local law, even if they are subject to the applicable DTA in are deemed to be resident in this other country; shares (voting rights) of persons for whom the personal requirements of Section 2 AStG (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "21) are given and who are resident in a low-tax area (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "22), unless the deadline for the extended limited tax liability has expired; indirect holdings, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the fraction of shares (voting rights) in the foreign company to be determined in accordance with Section 7 (2) AStG that is a person within the meaning of nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 via corporations, associations of persons, estates or partnerships that are not subject to unlimited tax liability; shares (voting rights) that are held by partnerships established in Germany or abroad, namely with the part that relates to the persons directly or indirectly involved in them in the sense the numbers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 are not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "722 When calculating the percentage that makes up the participations of the residents, the total issued shares of the foreign company must be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Treasury shares held by the foreign company itself are to be treated as unissued shares"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to shares through which foreign companies are involved in each other or in a ring"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to the above principles, there is full participation by the resident"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "74 Obligation to follow instructions741 Whether shares in a foreign company are attributable to a taxpayer is generally governed by civil law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, Sections 39 to 42 AO must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "742 The prerequisites for an attribution according to \u00a7 7 Abs 1 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 39 AO can apply in particular if a resident has shares held by a lawyer, notary, a credit institution or another intermediary based on a trust relationship or another relationship in such a way that he himself exercises actual control over the participation in such a way that he himself that as a rule he can economically exclude the formal owner from affecting the economic asset for the normal useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the resident actually excluded the formal owner from this influence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "An attribution according to \u00a7 7 Abs 1 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 42 AO is justified if Section 42 AO is to be applied to the involvement of the formal owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If natural persons are involved in this, the case law of the BFH on the involvement of companies must be consulted accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "743 When calculating the minimum participation in accordance with Section 7 (2) AStG, the amounts referred to in No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "741 and 742, shares or voting rights held by a person who has to follow the instructions of the unrestricted taxpayer or follow the instructions of the unrestricted taxpayer in such a way that they do not have any significant leeway for their own decisions must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is necessary, but also sufficient, that the authority or behavior to give instructions relates to the participation itself (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "on exercising voting rights at general meetings)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the addition of the income, however, the participation in the nominal capital is decisive (see BFH judgment of October 26, 1983 BStBl 1984 II, 258)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "76 Investment companies761 In addition to the cases of Section 7 (1) AStG, income with an investment character for which the foreign company is an intermediate company are already subject to additional taxation if an unrestricted taxpayer at least 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "holds a stake in the intermediate company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A control of the foreign company by unrestricted taxpayers and persons within the meaning of \u00a7 2 AStG is then not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Participation requires shares in the nominal capital of the foreign company under company law, which are held directly and indirectly by the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Shares attributable to the taxpayer according to Sections 39, 41, Paragraphs 2 and 42 AO constitute direct shareholdings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Indirect holdings exist if the taxpayer holds shares in the foreign company through partnerships (Section 7 (3) AStG) or if shares or voting rights are attributable to him under Section 7 (4) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the addition of the income, however, the participation in the nominal capital - also through partnerships - is decisive (see BFH judgment of October 26, 1983 BStBl 1984 II, 258)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is only no additional taxation in the context of the trivial regulation of Section 7 (6) sentence 2 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "762 The interim income with the character of an investment is to be determined in accordance with Section 10 Paragraph 1 to 4 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8 Income from intermediate companies80 Active activity and passive income801 Income from passive income is subject to additional taxation that is not from active activities within the meaning of Section 8 (1) No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 7 AStG or from the activity of a regional or functional holding company within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG and which are subject to low taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The question of which activities are attributable to a foreign company must be assessed according to general income tax principles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, an activity is to be assigned to the person for whose account it is carried out (BFH judgment of 1 July 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 222)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The qualification of the income is to be carried out according to the actual circumstances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant to which type of income within the meaning of Section 2 (1) EStG the income belongs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "802 In the case of a foreign company that is active in business, income may arise that - viewed in isolation - is income from passive income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Economically related activities are then to be uniformly subsumed (functional approach)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The decisive factor is the activity on which, according to the general public opinion, the economic focus lies (see BFH judgment of 16 May 1990 BStBl II, 1049)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, additional operating income arising in the context of an active overall activity must be allocated to the income from the active activity (cf. Section 76 Paragraph 9 KStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "These facts are to be presented by the taxpayer according to \u00a7 90 Abs 2 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Additional business income in this sense is given if the income belongs to an active activity according to the public opinion and this is the economic focus (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income from the financial resources necessary for active activity, income from renting company apartments or leasing storage areas of a commercial enterprise)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income is fully attributable to passive income if it is partly caused by an active activity, but the passive activity represents an area with an independent economic focus according to the public opinion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the same way, income with the character of an investment can be secondary income from other passive acquisitions when viewed from a functional perspective"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "803 If the foreign company is active within the framework of a uniform contract, the services it provides are detailed in accordance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "801 and 802 to qualify"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Uniform treatment is only possible insofar as the individual services are presented as a unit according to the general understanding of the public"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "804 If the foreign company holds a stake in a partnership, for the purposes of Section 8 AStG, the income flowing from the participation is to be treated as if the foreign company itself had carried out the activities from which the relevant profit of the partnership originates (see BFH Judgment of 16 May 1990 BStBl II, 1049)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81 Interim income 811 Agriculture and forestry Agriculture and forestry within the meaning of Section 8 (1) No. 1 AStG includes the agricultural and forestry activities of the foreign company including the sale of the assets used for this purpose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "812 Industrial activity 8121 The production, processing, processing or assembly of things, the generation of energy as well as the prospecting and extraction of mineral resources (industrial activity) are active activities outside of the addition taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "811 applies to them accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8122 If the foreign company has acquired, processed, processed and resold goods, then there is full industrial activity if the processing or processing, according to the prevailing opinion, has resulted in an object that is not marketable and the goods from the foreign company are not only marginal has been treated; a split into industrial activity and trade (Section 8 (1) No. 4 AStG) is out of the question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Labeling, repackaging, refilling, sorting, the compilation of purchased items into aggregates and the application of control characters do not count as processing or processing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the above-mentioned requirements are not met, there is full trading (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "814)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "813 Credit Institutions and Insurance Companies 8131 Credit Institutions are commercial companies that conduct business within the meaning of Section 1 (1) of the German Banking Act (KWG) and other business in the credit industry according to the prevailing view of the credit industry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8132 Insurance companies are commercial companies that conduct insurance business within the meaning of Section 1 of the Insurance Supervision Act in an insurance-economic manner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8133 Holding activities, asset management and the assumption of financial tasks within a group, in particular for the purpose of balancing risks, and comparable activities are not banking or insurance transactions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The purchase and collection of accounts receivable (factoring) is not to be considered as an operation of a credit institute if the acquisition of accounts receivable is exclusively or predominantly carried out by affiliated companies, because a banking activity typically requires a combination of various business and customer risks"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The operation of credit institutions does not include activities within the meaning of Section 1 (1) No. 6 KWG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8134 If funds are invested in land, participations and similar assets in connection with the operation of banking and insurance business, the income from this is to be considered as secondary income within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "802 to be dealt with insofar as there is a customary banking or insurance investment taking into account the principle of risk management"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8135 Credit institutions or insurance companies maintain a business set up for their business in a commercial manner, if the companies are equipped in terms of material and personnel so that they can conclude and carry out banking or insurance transactions with third parties to an extent that justifies a credit institution or insurance company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, active activity is also ruled out in this case if the banking or insurance business in question predominantly (i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to more than 50 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": ") are operated with a) unrestricted taxpayers who are involved in the company in accordance with Section 7 AStG, and / and b) unrestricted or limited taxpayers who are close to the unlimited taxpayer as defined in letter a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8136 Banking or insurance business is mainly carried out with this group of people if either the lending or deposit business or both are carried out with this group of people"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Subordinate transactions with third parties are not recognized if they cannot be borne by a credit institution or insurance company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Insurance companies that insure the group\u2019s risks operate the associated overall business with related parties even if they reinsure the risks assumed with third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the lending or deposit business is carried out with third parties to a not only insignificant extent, it must be determined according to the circumstances of the individual case whether the transactions with third parties or with domestic participants or persons closely related to them predominate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Here, the transactions are to be weighted according to economic aspects, whereby the importance of the related assets in the balance sheet can be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The business with the in Par"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8135 are always harmful if they do not correspond to the mix of business and customer risks or the principle of risk mix which the general public assumes in a credit or insurance business activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular if an intermediate company conducts banking or insurance business almost exclusively with its shareholders or their related parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "814 Trading8141 Trading as passive acquisition81411 In accordance with Section 8 (1) No. 4 AStG, trading is part of passive acquisition if the goods are delivered by a domestic shareholder or a related person from Germany or to a domestic partner or a related person in Germany becomes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, too, there is no passive acquisition if it can be proven that the commercial transaction is carried out by the foreign company as part of a \"qualified business operation\" (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142) has been made and there is no \"harmful involvement\" of a domestic participant or a related person in this commercial transaction (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8143) existed (sale or purchase of goods via foreign sales or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Purchasing companies)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81412 The activity of the commission agent is also regarded as trading"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the foreign company is active as a broker or commercial agent, the provisions on services are to be applied (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "815)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81413 If goods from abroad are sold abroad, transported through the country and only stored in Germany for reasons of transport, there is neither a domestic delivery nor a domestic delivery"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142 Commercial business operations and participation in general economic activity 81421 The foreign company maintains a commercially established business operation (\"qualified business operation\") if it is equipped in terms of material and personnel to prepare the commercial transactions under consideration while participating in general economic relations , complete and execute"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Participation in general commercial transactions must start from the business of the foreign company itself, which leads to the income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Indirect participation in commercial transactions via dependent group companies is not sufficient (see the BFH judgment of 29 August 1984 on the service sector, BStBl 1985 II, 120)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81422 Participation in general commercial transactions occurs when the company turns to an indefinite number of people in its business operations for the commercial transactions in question to a not only insignificant extent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient if the company only contacts an indefinite number of people when selling or purchasing the goods, but only purchases the goods from a company closely related to it or delivers it to such a company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81423 Participation in general commercial transactions is also given if the indefinite number of customers is limited to a narrow group of people due to the subject of the business activity in question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Likewise, the limitation to a narrow group of customers is harmless if the foreign company does not commit itself to a strictly limited group of people, but its business operations are geared towards changing customers (see BFH judgment of 29 August 1984 BStBl 1985 II, 120)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is harmless if the customer base of a foreign company that supplies spare parts is limited to people who are buyers of a company closely related to the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8143 Personal participation 81431 A person participates in a commercial transaction of the foreign company if he or she carries out activities which, according to their function, are part of the preparation, conclusion or execution of the relevant transactions of this company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the remuneration for these services has been calculated as between independent third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If individual transactions of subordinate importance arise in the course of active trading activities in which a domestic participant or a closely related person is involved, an examination of whether passive acquisition is present can be omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, \u00a7 1 AStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A person contributes when they e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "takes on sales for the foreign company, manages the deployment of representatives, takes on their financing tasks or bears their trading risk"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81432 Participation is e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "not before if a manufacturer or supplier in transactions, the preparation, conclusion or execution of which is otherwise handled by the foreign company, sends goods generally or in individual cases directly to customers of the foreign company in a manner practiced between independent trading companies (drop shipping) or surrenders to the foreign company goods that remain in its ownership for resale (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Delivery to a consignment warehouse maintained by the foreign company); provides the customers of the foreign company with ancillary services that are necessary for proper delivery in the opinion of the general public (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "technical instruction of customers by the manufacturer); generally advertises goods manufactured or supplied by the manufacturer or supplier without contacting the trading company's customers (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Advertising campaigns for branded goods)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A normal commercial activity as a supplier, such as direct delivery by the manufacturer or ensuring timely delivery specifications by the buyer (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "for \"just-in-time delivery\"), is harmless; \u00a7 1 AStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "815 Services 8151 Services as passive acquisition 81511 Pursuant to Section 8 (1) No. 5 AStG, the provision of services by the foreign company is part of the passive acquisition insofar as the service is provided by the foreign company using a domestic participant or a related person ( Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81521)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the foreign company maintains a \"qualified business\" or whether a domestic participant or a closely related person receives the service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as this fact only comes into consideration, passive acquisition is ruled out if it can be proven that the services have been provided within the framework of a \"qualified business operation\" of the company and that the domestic participant or the related person did not participate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Financial services within a group lead to passive acquisition, unless they fall under Section 8 (1) No. 3 or No. 7 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81512 The provision of services in cases of Section 8 (1) No. 5 (b) AStG is no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8152 Provision of services through the services of others 81521 The foreign company uses a person for the service in question if it uses this person in order to fulfill its own obligations to provide or provide this service in whole or in a not only insignificant part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient if the person involved does not contribute to the service himself, but through the use of staff or facilities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The person can work as an employee or in some other way (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "as self-employed); it can also be a corporation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81522 A related person is taxable in Germany on their income from the service they have contributed if they are fully taxable on the income from their contribution to the foreign company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies in the case of extended limited tax liability according to \u00a7 2 AStG (see BFH judgment of 29 August 1984 BStBl 1985 II, 120)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8153 Own participation 81531 A foreign company provides a person with a service if the person receives the service directly or has it performed by a third party"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81532 Participation in the activities belonging to the service occurs when a person carries out activities that, according to their function, belong to the effect of this service, in particular by participating in the service by providing staff or facilities or by planning the service in whole or in a not only insignificant part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the remuneration for this service has been calculated as between independent third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If individual transactions of minor importance arise in the course of active activity, in which a domestic participant or a closely related person is involved, an examination of whether passive acquisition is present can be omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, \u00a7 1 AStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "816 Renting and leasing 8161 In accordance with Section 8 (1) No. 6 AStG, renting and leasing are passive acquisitions unless one of the three following exceptions applies: the exploitation of one's own research or development work that was undertaken without harmful involvement; the renting and leasing of real estate if the income from it would be tax-free if the taxpayer obtained it directly on the basis of a double taxation agreement and the renting and leasing of movable property in the context of a \"qualified business\" without any harmful involvement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8162 Item no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8163 A person participates in the renting or leasing of movable property of the foreign company if he carries out activities which, according to his function, are part of the commercial renting or leasing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "So is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "participation is given if a person takes over the maintenance and financing tasks for a foreign company or mediates the conclusion of the rental or lease agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "81532 sentences 2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8164 Finance leasing is not a rental or leasing, but a credit transaction, provided that the leasing object is attributable to the lessee according to the existing principles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "817 Raising and lending foreign capital 8171 Raising and lending capital is only an active acquisition if the foreign company can be shown to have raised the capital exclusively on foreign capital markets and as a loan to companies located abroad (permanent establishments) that receive exclusively or almost exclusively gross income from active acquisition, or to establishments located in Germany (permanent establishments)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise there is passive acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8172 The capital is raised on foreign capital markets within the meaning of Section 8 (1) No. 7 AStG if it comes from the issuance of bonds exclusively on foreign capital markets, is obtained by taking out loans from foreign credit collection agencies or is otherwise available to persons on foreign capital markets who are based abroad and there is no indirect borrowing on the domestic capital market"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When raising capital, the absorbing company itself must have entered the foreign capital market"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not sufficient if related parties within the meaning of \u00a7 1 AStG are involved in raising capital as trustees or representatives without them disclosing to the investors in whose interests they are acting"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Capital made available by persons closely related to the taxpayer or the foreign company is not considered to be raised on foreign capital markets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a bond consortium, to which residents belong, participates in the issuance of bonds in the usual banking manner, this is harmless provided the bond is actually placed on the foreign capital markets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8173 A capital injection within the meaning of Section 8 (1) No. 7 AStG exists if the foreign company lends the capital to a company maintained in Germany (maintained permanent establishment) or a company maintained abroad (maintained permanent establishment), in the latter case under the additional condition that the institution can demonstrate that its gross income is exclusively or almost exclusively from activities within the meaning of Section 8 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 6 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is no loan allocation if the capital is used by the foreign company to acquire equity interests or rights equivalent to these, or for contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the loan-like addition according to the direct method cannot be allocated to the capital raised, the total amount of the loan not allocated is to be allocated in the ratio of equity capital including accumulated income to borrowed capital using the indirect method and the proportion of the borrowed capital corresponding to the borrowed capital allocated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 8 (1) No. 7 AStG, the prerequisite is that the capital is allocated to companies or permanent establishments operated abroad which generate their gross income exclusively or almost exclusively from active activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is based on the circumstances of the financial year in which the foreign company as the lender generates the corresponding income from the surrender of the capital"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This means that in individual cases the qualification of the income from the loan donation can change from financial year to financial year at the lender, depending on whether the borrower achieves gross income from exclusively or almost exclusively active activities in his business or his permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8174 When applying \u00a7 8 Paragraph 1 No. 7 AStG, the following must also be observed for the capital injection: According to \u00a7 8 Paragraph 1 No. 7 AStG a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the capital raised must be \"permanently\" allocated to companies or permanent establishments outside the scope of the law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The capital may not be used in companies or permanent establishments in Germany, not even temporarily"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The term \"in the long term\" presupposes a longer period of time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to the regulation for long-term debts within the meaning of \u00a7 8 No. 1 and \u00a7 12 Paragraph 2 No. 1 GewStG, according to which debts with a term of more than one year are generally regarded as continuous debts (Section 47 GewStR 1990), the capital is to be regarded as \"permanently\" added if a year is exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Only in special cases (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in the event of early repayment of the loan due to unforeseen circumstances), if this period is not reached, capital may be added \"permanently\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This applies up to and including the assessment period 1992. 82 Regional and functional holding 821 According to Section 8 (2) AStG, profit shares that a foreign company receives from participations in certain active foreign subsidiaries are equated with income from active activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The foreign company must have an uninterrupted share of at least a quarter of the nominal capital of the subsidiary company at least twelve months before the closing date that is decisive for determining the profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income from a participation within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG also includes a) Income from a hidden profit distribution (see BFH judgment of 29 August 1984 BStBl 1985 II, 120) or \"other monetary benefits\", such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Bonus shares, bonuses which are due to the participation under company law, b) Profits and losses from the dissolution of the subsidiary company, from the sale of participations in it or payments from capital reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "822 For profit distributions within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG and for the question of active activity, the relevant financial year is the year specified in the profit distribution resolution (see Section 76 (10) KStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The principles of Section 26 Paragraphs 2 to 5 KStG apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a misuse of design is to be suspected, a decision must be made according to the circumstances of the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Was z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If an active activity was created for the company only for the year of the distribution - without economic reason - this structure is not recognized for tax purposes according to \u00a7 42 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "823 There is an economic connection within the meaning of Section 8 (2) No. 2 AStG if a participation is held due to the foreign company's own active activities (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Participation of the production company in the sale of the goods it manufactures)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not enough for the participation to be held to promote the interests of a third party"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "An economic interest that is only aimed at holding equity interests is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "824 companies that are economically subordinate to a foreign group company with an active overall character (functional company) must"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "are held directly by domestic group companies for non-tax reasons; a functional holding within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG does not exist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In such cases, interim income of the foreign company is to be exempted from the addition in the amount determined in accordance with Section 14, Paragraph 1, last sentence AStG, if it comes from activities or objects that a person under Section 8, Paragraph 1 Nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 6 AStG, the foreign functional company serves its own activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The tax liability of distributions by the foreign company remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "83 Low taxation 831 Income tax burden 8311 Income from passive acquisitions is subject to additional taxation if in the state of the management or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "of the registered office of the foreign company (country of domicile) the total income tax burden (income tax burden) below 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "is (\u00a7 8 Abs 3 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes from other countries are not to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: A low taxation can result from the fact that the foreign company in a highly taxing country takes advantage of targeted tax breaks for passive income (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 986)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Merely shifting the tax liability over time due to depreciation rates that are generally customary abroad or similar regulations that balance each other out in the foreseeable future may not be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the special features of profit distributions, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "833 8312 Income taxes within the meaning of Section 8 (3) AStG are all taxes in the country of domicile on total income or on parts of the income, including taxes on profits from the sale of movable or immovable property and taxes on capital growth"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Such taxes must also be taken into account if they cannot be offset according to Section 34c EStG or Section 26 KStG, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "because they are collected in accordance with the laws of a province, canton or other regional authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes that are withheld by the foreign company at the expense of third parties (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Capital gains taxes on their profit distributions) are not recognized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The special circumstances in Switzerland are dealt with in the BMF letter of 23 May 1980 (BStBl I, 282)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "832 Determination of the income tax burden 8321 The income tax burden generally corresponds to the income tax rate of the country of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When determining the income tax burden, not only the general tariff, but also possible preferential rates and exemptions for income from passive income or for companies without active activities and the tax base must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8322 The Federal Minister of Finance, in agreement with the highest tax authorities of the federal states, determines the areas that are eligible for the application of Section 8 (3) AStG in which tax rates or preferential rates are below 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "or tax exemptions within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8321 exist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Appendix 1: Appendix 1 contains a compilation of the rates of income taxes, tax breaks and privileges in areas that are particularly relevant for the application of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Annex 2: Annex 2 8323 contains an overview of other areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8321 underlying rate less than 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": ", the income tax burden can nonetheless be above this limit, in particular because the foreign company has not claimed any preferential rates or exemptions or the income in question in the country of domicile has been included in the tax base with an amount that is higher than when applying the German tax law would be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the income tax burden is to be determined by comparing the interim income determined under German tax law and the taxes payable in the country of domicile of the foreign company (debit calculation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8324 If the amount according to para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8321 underlying sentence 30 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "or more, the income tax burden can nonetheless be below this limit, in particular because the foreign company has received special reductions and exemptions (e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "on the basis of tax contracts) or the relevant income in the country of domicile has been included in the tax base with an amount that is lower than would have been assessed under German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the income tax burden is calculated by means of a burden calculation (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8323 sentence 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8325 When calculating the burden, it is not taken into account that the tax in the country of domicile is below the minimum limit of Section 8 (3) AStG because the taxation of one year takes into account losses in the same year or earlier or later years (loss deduction, carryforward or carry-back ); on the taxes of the foreign companies according to principles which correspond to those of \u00a7 34c EStG and \u00a7 26 Abs 1 KStG, taxes of other countries or German taxes have been credited or such taxes have been deducted from the assessment base"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8326 For the purposes of the debit calculation, no objection can be made if economic goods belonging to a \"qualified business operation\" (Tz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142) are used for trading, the provision of services or the rental or leasing of movable property, have been valued in accordance with the provisions of foreign tax law, which correspond to the general German profit determination regulations and are generally used as the basis for taxation in the country of domicile"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This must not lead to an obviously incorrect result in the load calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "833 Low taxation of dividends 8331 A profit distribution that the foreign company receives is always taxed at a low level if it is exempt from taxes in the country of domicile due to a box privilege or if the country of domicile is entitled to its tax on the profit distribution by way of \"indirect tax credit\" \"Offsets taxes on profits paid by the distributing company; In this case, the actual load conditions are irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8332 In the case of other profit distributions, according to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "832 to decide whether there is low taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8333 profit distributions, to which no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8331 or \u00a7 13 AStG is to be applied and the tax of the country of domicile of these are excluded when determining the income tax burden for the other income from passive acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "834 Low taxation for mixed income For foreign companies with mixed income, the above regulations apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "To calculate the burden, the tax in the country of domicile must be determined, which is attributable to the income from passive acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The procedure for dividing the taxes required for this is as follows: If certain income has been exempted, taxed at a preferential rate or taxed at a higher rate in the country of domicile, the foreign tax is to be applied to the amount that actually applies to it, taking these advantages into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the remaining income, the remaining tax must be taken into account proportionally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the allocation, the income from active activity and from passive acquisition are to be taken into account in the amount in which they are based on the taxation of the country of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9 Exemption limit for mixed income 901 Exemption limit according to gross income For the determination of gross income, the principles to be observed in Section 26 KStG apply accordingly (reference to Section 76 Paragraph 8 and 9 KStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Concealed deposits do not generate any gross income from activities within the meaning of Section 8 Paragraph 1 Nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 7 AStG or from participations within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG (BFH judgment of 1 July 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 222)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "902 Absolute exemption limit of 120000 DM 9021 The absolute exemption limit of \u00a7 9 AStG refers to the additional amount within the meaning of \u00a7 10 Paragraph 1 AStG, which would be applied if the exemption limit did not exist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Intermediate income from a downstream intermediate company, which is attributable to a foreign company according to Section 14 AStG, must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9022 The exemption limit is exceeded with regard to the company as such if the additional amounts for all domestic participants exceed the amount of DM 120,000; with regard to a domestic participant, if the additional amounts for all foreign companies in which he is involved exceed the amount of 120,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This does not exclude that other domestic participants who are involved in the company can make use of the exemption limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9023 The absolute exemption limit, insofar as it relates to the company, is based on the relevant financial year; insofar as it relates to a domestic participant, it is based on the assessment period in which the additional amounts in question are to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9024 If the exemption limit, insofar as it relates to a domestic participant, is not exceeded in individual cases, this must be taken into account when assessing the domestic participant even if the notification of the separate determination according to \u00a7 18 AStG does not contain a corresponding reservation (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18126)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "903 Profit shares 9031 When checking whether the exemption limit according to \u00a7 9 AStG has been exceeded in companies with mixed income, profit shares that fall under \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 AStG are not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The profit shares are to be deducted both from the total amount of gross income and from the gross income on which the income from passive acquisition is based"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9032 The profit distributions themselves are to be treated according to \u00a7 13 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, it is not objectionable if Section 9 AStG is applied to them, provided that the exemption limits provided in this provision are not exceeded, including the profit shares"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10 Additional amount100 Overview1001 When determining the assessment basis for the application of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG, the total income of the intermediate company from passive acquisition (minus taxes) must be determined; the profit shares for which this is provided for in accordance with \u00a7 13 AStG are to be excluded from this; Losses are to be deducted (section 10 (3) sentence 5 AStG); the resulting amounts are to be divided among the individual domestic participants (persons obliged to add additional amounts); the surcharges and deductions to be made for the individual additional amounts that the individual persons obliged to add according to sections 11 and 12 AStG affect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "To take into account income that is to be recognized in accordance with Section 14 AStG, cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "141002 The exemption from box dividends according to \u00a7 13 AStG takes precedence over loss deduction as a factual tax exemption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, the profit shares within the meaning of Section 13 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 No. 1 Letter a, Section 13 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 No. 2 and Section 13 Paragraph 2 AStG are to be excluded when determining the income from passive acquisition and only then to deduct the losses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1003 The individual steps in determining the tax bases for the application of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 Appendix 3 AStG result from the calculation overviews in Appendix 31004 The legal consequences essential for the application of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG are through uniform and separate determination according to \u00a7 18 AStG to decide (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "101 Determination of the additional amount1011 Determination of the income from passive acquisition10111 For the additional taxation, the total income of the foreign intermediate company that originates from passive acquisition must be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of German tax law apply accordingly to the determination of income (Section 10 (3) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 1 AStG does not apply to the determination of the income on which the additional amount is based (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10112 If, in terms of legal form or activity, the foreign company corresponds to the taxpayers named in Section 8 (2) KStG, the entire income is to be treated as income from commercial operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the company realizes capital gains that would not be taxable in the hands of the party obliged to add them as profits from the sale of private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the parties involved cannot refer to Section 42 AO in order to eliminate the disadvantageous tax consequences caused by the involvement of the foreign company (see BFH judgment of July 12, 1989 BStBl 1990 II, 113)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10113 If a resident taxpayer has a direct interest in several foreign intermediate companies, losses of one intermediate company may not be compensated with positive additional amounts from another intermediate company (consequence of Section 10 (1) sentence 3 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "To compensate for losses of downstream companies or intermediate companies with positive income of the parent company, reference is made to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1416 and 1417 pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10114 If the income from passive acquisitions is initially determined in a foreign currency (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10323), they are to be converted according to the rate at the time at which the additional amount is deemed to have accrued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a rate cannot be determined at this point in time, the official rate determination for the point in time which is closest to the end of the relevant financial year of the foreign company is to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not objectionable if an annual average rate is used as the basis for the conversion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The exchange rate chosen for the conversion is to be observed for all amounts in foreign currency to be taken into account when applying Sections 7 to 11 and Sections 13 and 14 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the principles developed for Section 34c (1) EStG and Section 26 (1) KStG apply to the deduction of foreign taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Once chosen, the method of conversion should not be changed without sufficient reason"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The above statements apply mutatis mutandis to the conversion of loss deduction amounts to be determined separately in accordance with Section 10d (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1012 Deduction of taxes 10121 According to Section 10 (1) AStG, the taxes levied on the income of foreign companies can be deducted; the taxes levied on the assets on which this income is based, Section 102 (1) VStR 1993 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes on interim income with the character of an investment within the meaning of Section 10 (6) sentence 3 AStG are only 60 percent of the amount due to the reduced consideration of this income in the addition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "deduct"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In addition to taxes in the source country of the income - including German withholding taxes - taxes in the country of residence and from third countries are also deductible; Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8312 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10122 If the company has mixed income, the part of the foreign taxes on income and wealth must be deducted which is on the income or income subject to additional taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the assets underlying this income do not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The income taxes are here in the corresponding application of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "834 split"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not objectionable if the resulting relationship is also used as a basis for the distribution of wealth tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "103 Determination of profits in the case of purely intermediate companies 1031 Types of profit determination 10311 Profits subject to addition can be determined according to Section 10 Paragraph 3 Sentence 2 AStG by means of an asset comparison according to Section 4 Paragraph 1 Section 5 EStG or an income surplus calculation according to Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The right to choose is to be exercised until the declaration for the uniform and separate determination according to \u00a7 18 AStG is submitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the domestic participants do not exercise their right to vote or do so not at all, the profits are to be determined by comparing assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10312 If the type of profit determination is changed, R 17 Paragraph 1 and 3 EStR 1983 shall apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A change may not be made arbitrarily"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10313 If interim income is determined in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG, an inflow to the foreign intermediate company must always be assumed if a participant, a person closely related to this company or - in the interests of this person - a third party credits the company with amounts or makes the amounts available in another way are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Far-reaching provisions remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1032 Determination in accordance with Section 4 (1), Section 5 of the Income Tax Act 10321 The income on which the additional amount is based, in accordance with Section 4 (1), Section 5 of the Income Tax Act, is to be determined by means of an \"additional balance sheet\" applicable to all domestic participants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is based on the entire assets of the foreign company, even if not all shares or voting rights are attributable to residents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The additional balance sheet can be derived from the balance sheet of the foreign company in accordance with the accounting regulations to be observed under German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, \u00a7 60 EStDV applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10322 The German principles apply to the additional balance sheet even if foreign law allows different balance sheet approaches"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The principle of the balance sheet connection must also be observed if the foreign intermediate company is not bound by it in its own accounting or if no additions have to be made during individual years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10323 The additional balance sheet can be drawn up in the currency in which the foreign company's books are kept"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If this is a foreign currency, then No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1011410324 If the income from a \"qualified business operation\" maintained by a foreign company with participation in general economic activity (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8142) of the trade, the provision of services or the renting or leasing of movable items for the determination of profits, it may be permitted that provisions of foreign tax law are used as a basis that correspond to the general German profit determination regulations and are generally used as the basis for taxation in the country of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This must not lead to an obviously incorrect result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the application of foreign tax law would lead to interim income subject to additional taxation according to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10322 fall out of the additional taxation due to the end of the additional taxation, the business closure or similar processes, they are to be taxed in the last relevant financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1033 Opening balance sheet 10331 If the requirements for an addition are met for the first time with regard to a foreign company, an \"opening addition balance sheet\" must be drawn up at the beginning of the relevant financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The values \u200b\u200bstated in it apply to financial years that end after the key date of the opening balance sheet as amortized acquisition or production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10332 The following applies to the individual assets that are to be recognized as business assets: Fixed assets are to be recognized at their original acquisition or production costs (see BFH judgment of July 12, 1989 BStBl 1990 II, 113)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of depreciable fixed assets, these amounts are to be reduced by the deductions for wear and tear or depreciation of substance, which are to be measured according to \u00a7 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the partial amount is lower on the key date of the opening balance sheet, this value may be used at most if there is a significant, likely permanent decrease in value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A value may only be set for intangible assets if they were acquired against payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Current assets are to be reported at their acquisition or production costs, but at most with the partial value on the key date of the opening balance sheet, if this is lower than the acquisition or production costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Liabilities are generally to be stated at their repayment amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Deferred items are to be recognized if operating expenses prior to the balance sheet date are expenses and operating income prior to the balance sheet date are income for a certain period after the key date of the opening balance sheet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of assets that were already available on July 21, 1948, there is no objection to assuming the value with which the assets were listed in the first balance sheet of the foreign company drawn up after this point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, this must not lead to obviously incorrect results"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10333 Acquisition costs of an asset are the expenses that the company has made for the acquisition of the asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The following must be observed in particular: The cost of an asset that has been acquired in exchange is to be set at the average value of the asset given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If, in addition, a value adjustment has been paid, the acquisition costs increase by the value adjustment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of an asset acquired free of charge, the acquisition costs are to be set at the common value at the time of the free acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10332 No. 1 sentence 4 as well as No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10334 remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition costs of an asset that was brought into the company against the granting of shares in the company are generally to be assessed at the fair value at the time of the contribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of assets that the company has acquired as part of the free transfer of a business or part of a business, the cost of acquisition is the amount that was recognized when determining the profit of the previous (domestic) company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of assets that have been acquired against the granting of an annuity, the present value of the pension obligation may represent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "increased by any purchase price payment, the acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Production costs of an asset are the expenses incurred through the consumption of goods and the use of services for the production of the asset (see R 33 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10334 If the foreign company's assets were transferred from business assets by a domestic participant or a person closely related to him, the acquisition or production costs or the common value are based on the amount on which these persons are based for taxation when the asset is removed from their business assets have laid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If it is demonstrated that this approach is incorrect, this can be taken into account as soon as the approach for the transferor can still be changed in accordance with the principles of balance sheet adjustment (see R 15 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This applies accordingly to major participations within the meaning of Section 17 EStG that have been transferred from private assets to the foreign company; for assets that were transferred to domestic property or otherwise into private assets or foreign business assets before the transfer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1034 Income surplus calculation 10341 If the interim income of a foreign company is determined in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG, the profit is the excess of operating income over operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This type of profit determination can only be selected for the total income from passive acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "All assets of the foreign company used for passive acquisition are to be treated as necessary business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is no room for the application of R 16 (6) EStR 1993"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10342 The operating expenses also include the deductions for wear and tear according to \u00a7 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10343 The deduction of losses is also permitted when determining profits in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1035 Losses 10351 Losses in other relevant financial years from passive acquisitions can be deducted from the income on which the additional amount is based, in accordance with Section 10d EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Losses that arose from interim income within the meaning of Section 10 (6) sentence 3 AStG are only 60 percent of the amount due to the reduced consideration of this income in the addition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "deduct"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The loss deduction is after deduction of taxes that have been levied on the foreign company on this income and on the assets on which this income is based, and after application of Section 13 AStG and before application of the absolute exemption limit of Section 9 AStG and Section 11 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The deductible taxes for the year of the loss are to be included in the determination of the loss, unless they have been offset; Reference to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1011310352 The loss carryforward is not excluded by the fact that no income from passive acquisitions was accrued in a year following the year in which the loss occurred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10353 A change in the shareholders of the foreign company affects the amount of the deductible loss carry-back or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "- not lecture at the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10354 Losses of the following years do not need to be deducted from interim income of one year, which according to Section 11 (1) AStG is to be reduced by distributions from this year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "These losses can then be deducted in accordance with the rules of Section 10d EStG in the year following the loss incurred (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18127)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "104 Determination of profits for companies with mixed income 1041 If the foreign company has mixed income, the income from passive acquisition is to be differentiated as follows: The total of the income from active activity contained therein is to be deducted from the total amount of the company's income determined according to German tax law (total calculation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Notwithstanding No. 1, the income can be made up by a separate partial balance sheet or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income surplus regulation are determined if they can be easily and clearly recorded separately from the other income on the basis of the accounting of the intermediate company (special determination)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1042 Are active activities and passive income so closely linked (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "active and passive trading) that the income from active activity cannot be shown separately, the total income must be divided up according to turnover, if the relevant division criteria are not given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1043 In the case of the special investigation and the distribution of income according to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1042, the parties involved are obliged to provide all information about the active activity and to provide all evidence that is necessary for the full recording and delimitation of the income from passive income on request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1044 Examples: If, in addition to income from passive acquisitions, a foreign asset management company also receives interest and dividends that fall under Section 8 Paragraph 1 No. 7 or Paragraph 2 AStG, the total income must first be determined and then the stated interest and dividends, reduced by the related operating expenses or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Business expenses to be deducted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a foreign company generates profits from production activities and income from passive acquisitions that can be easily separated from it, such as income from securities or participations, the determination of the total income can be dispensed with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, it is sufficient to separately determine the income from passive acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a foreign company sells goods in active trading at different margins than in passive trading, then in the case of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1042 for the determination of the income from passive acquisition of the total profit according to the respective sales taking into account the trading margins, unless the application of another method leads to an appropriate result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "105 Application of double taxation agreements 1051 For the application of a double taxation agreement between the Federal Republic of Germany and the country of domicile of the intermediate company, the additional amount is treated like a profit distribution (Section 10 (5) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In principle, it is subject to German taxation without restriction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1052 If the agreement provides for exemption from German tax (DBA box privilege) for profit distributions that accrue to a significantly participating German corporation from a company in the other country, the additional amount is in accordance with the agreement applicable in relation to the country of domicile of the foreign company to be released"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted here that many agreements restrict the DBA box privilege to distributions from active companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the DBA box privilege only extends to corporation tax, the additional amount is only to be applied to trade tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the amount of the minimum participation, Section 8b (5) KStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1053 Are shares in a foreign intermediate company not attributable to the civil law owner but to a third party with unlimited tax liability (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 or 42 AO), the relationship between this third party and the intermediate company determines whether a DBA box privilege is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1054 If there are doubts as to whether a DBA box privilege is to be granted to the foreign company for its distributions according to the circumstances in the country of domicile, they must be clarified in the information procedure, if necessary in the mutual agreement procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1055 If the additional amount includes income from downstream intermediate companies within the meaning of Section 14 AStG, the exemption only applies subject to the restrictions of Section 14 (4) AStG if it would be tax-exempt under the DTA even if the taxpayer had a direct participation in the subsidiary company; see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1441056 If a share in a foreign company is part of the business assets of a permanent establishment located in a DBA state, the exemption to be granted under the relevant DBA according to Section 10 (5) AStG also extends to the additional amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the share is actually attributable to the permanent establishment (see BFH judgment of February 26, 1992 BStBl II, 937)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the permanent establishment is a control or coordination body, the principles of the BMF letter of August 24, 1984 (Federal Law Gazette I, 458) are to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "106 Interim income with the character of an investment1061 According to Section 10 (6) AStG, interim income with the character of an investment is subject to taxation even if there is a double taxation agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A distinction must be made here between income with the nature of an investment within the meaning of Section 10 (6) sentence 2 and that within the meaning of Section 10 (6) sentence 3 AStG; the latter are only in the amount of 60 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to be taken into account when determining the additional amount (reference to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1066)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1062 According to Section 10 (6) sentence 2 AStG, interim income with the character of an investment is income from the passive acquisition of a foreign company that comes from holding, managing, maintaining or increasing the value of means of payment, receivables, securities, participations or similar assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This is income within the meaning of \u00a7 20 EStG as well as income from finance leasing (reference to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "8164), insofar as it is not a rental activity, factoring, financial innovations and forward transactions that are taxed low, unless the taxpayer indicates the existence of one of the exceptions in Section 10 (6) sentence 2 nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 3 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Investment income also includes corresponding capital gains and losses, as well as ancillary income that can be functionally allocated to investment income, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "from hedging transactions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the determination according to \u00a7 10 Abs 6 AStG a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Whether the interim income of the capital investment character predominates - up to and including the assessment period 1992 - is based on the ratio of this income to the total interim income of the foreign intermediate company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1063 No interim income with the character of an investment is income within the meaning of Section 8 (1) No. 3 AStG from capital investments by credit institutions or insurance companies, with the exception of Section 8 (1) No. 7 and Section 8 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income that has the character of an investment in itself is to be allocated to income from active activity if it is directly economically related to the active activity (reference to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "802) 1064 If the relevant evidence is provided, the income of a company holding company does not constitute interim income with the character of an investment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The exception of Section 10, Paragraph 6, Sentence 2, No. 2 AStG extends to the income from the participation, including the profits from the sale of this participation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1065 The exception in section 10 (6) sentence 2 number 3 AStG concerns income for intragroup services that consist of holding, managing and maintaining the value of assets, which are appropriately remunerated in accordance with section 1 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the foreign company is active within the framework of a uniform contract, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "803 referenced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1066 With appropriate evidence, interim income with the character of an investment according to Section 10 (6) sentence 3 AStG is only 60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to be applied if they come from the intra-group financing of foreign permanent establishments and companies belonging to the group, regardless of where these funds come from"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the permanent establishments or companies located abroad generate their gross income exclusively or almost exclusively from activities within the meaning of Section 8 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 6 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The decisive criterion for belonging to a foreign permanent establishment or foreign company is uniform management"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Only in the amount of 60 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The portion of interim income with the character of an investment within the meaning of Section 10 Paragraph 6 Sentence 3 AStG is not subject to trade tax (Section 21 Paragraph 7 Sentence 2 No. 2 AStG) or wealth tax (Section 20 Paragraph 3 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1067 The legal consequence of Section 10 (6) AStG only applies if the additional amount includes interim income with the nature of an investment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the additional amount consists of both interim investment income and other income, it is to be divided into a part that is to be exempted according to Section 10 (5) AStG and a part not exempted according to Section 10 (6) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to the principles of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "104 to proceed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Have interim income with investment character led to the additional amount and this is reduced, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "by deducting losses according to \u00a7 10d EStG or by adding negative interim income with investment character from sub-companies, it can be assumed - if a direct allocation is not possible - that the reduction is proportionally due to the different interim income with investment character"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "11 Distribution of profit shares110 Taxation of the distribution1101 Profit shares that the foreign company distributes to unlimited taxpayers (including hidden profit distributions) are subject to taxation in accordance with the general provisions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of Sections 7 to 14 AStG - with the exception of the regulation in Section 11 (4) sentence 2 AStG - do not affect their taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1102 In principle, only the tax levied on the distributions at the expense of the unrestricted taxpayer (capital gains tax) in accordance with Section 34c EStG or Section 26 KStG and any applicable DTAs can be offset against the income (corporation) tax on the profit shares"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A crediting of taxes of the foreign company itself, as provided for in \u00a7 12 AStG in the context of additional taxation, is not applicable; the regulations of the DBA and \u00a7 26 KStG for box dividends remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1103 If the distribution consists of a hidden profit distribution, it can happen that it is drawn in a year in which an additional amount is not yet considered to have accrued due to the provision of Section 10 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the distribution can be reduced from the additional amount for the following year in accordance with Section 11 (1) AStG for reasons of equity (avoidance of double taxation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A reduction can also be made for advance distributions and for cases in which the activation of the future profit claim means that the distribution is recorded earlier"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "111 Reduction in accordance with Section 11 (1) AStG1111 The reduction in accordance with Section 11 (1) AStG is based on the amount of the distribution before deduction of capital gains taxes and similar charges borne by the recipient"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The distribution is also to be deducted in full if the foreign company has received distributable income from active activity in addition to the interim income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Hidden profit distributions within the meaning of German tax law are equivalent to distributions (reference to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1103)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The payout is offset against the additional amount at the rate at which the income from passive acquisitions on which the additional amount is based was converted (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10114)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1112 Does an unrestricted taxpayer receive additional income in a manner other than through distribution (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "through the sale or withdrawal of the shares in the intermediate company, through capital repayment or in the context of a liquidation of the intermediate company, through capital repayment or in the context of the liquidation of an intermediate company), a reduction or reimbursement according to \u00a7 11 Paragraph 1 and 2 AStG is not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the event of sales, however, reimbursement is possible within the framework of Section 11 (3) AStG; this provision is to be applied accordingly in the case of withdrawal and liquidation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if the contribution or contribution of shares in the foreign company leads to taxation of the hidden reserves that have been discovered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1113 The legal consequence of Section 11 (1) AStG, even if applied accordingly, based on Section 14 (2) AStG, only comes into effect in the calendar year or financial year in which the attributable interim income is to be recognized as part of an additional amount according to Section 10 (2) AStG (BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "112 Tax reimbursement according to Section 11 (2) AStG1121 The tax reimbursement according to Section 11 (2) AStG is based on the following no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "111 distributions to be taken into account for a year, less the additional amount within the meaning of Section 10 (1) AStG for the same year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A distribution surplus can also result if an addition according to Section 10 (1) sentence 3 AStG is not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, an additional amount of zero can be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A tax refund based on a loss carry-back according to Section 10 (3) sentence 5 AStG takes precedence over the tax refund according to Section 11 (2) and (3) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If taxes according to \u00a7 12 AStG or \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 Letter b AStG have been credited for a previous year, the additional amount must be reduced by the amounts by which it was increased with regard to the crediting when applying sentence 5"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1122 Income from passive acquisition, which has been left out of account according to \u00a7 9 AStG, reduce the profit shares entitling to tax refund in the amount of the additional amount to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1123 For each previous year, according to Section 11 (2) AStG, the total income tax or corporation tax due for the respective previous year on the additional amount to be applied and not yet reimbursed according to Section 11 AStG (minus any"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 12 AStG and \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 Letter b AStG) as well as the trade tax are reimbursed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The reimbursement amount must be determined on the basis of a fictitious assessment of the calendar year in which the reimbursement-triggering addition was made, without affecting the taxation of this calendar year (so-called shadow assessment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the reimbursement amounts, the difference between the tax amounts that resulted from an assessment once with and once without taking into account the additional amount is to be compared with the tax that would have resulted if only the additional amount reduced by the profit shares was included in the tax base would be (see BFH judgment of 10 March 1982 BStBl 1983 II, 14)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For procedural handling, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18151124 The distribution surplus of one year must be offset against several additional amounts not yet offset (HZB) according to their chronological order"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: Year123456HZB1000500500500500500Distribution300100800800800HZB according to \u00a7 11 AStG1000200400000Distribution surplus --- 300300300Taxes are to be reimbursed112 (200) of the year3 (100) HZB still to be offset for the year 110007004000year 22000 of the domestic tax law participant in an additional \u00a710,000 reduced, the tax of the following year for which the reduction in the loss deduction had a tax effect can be used as a basis for the reimbursement pursuant to Section 11 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the years mentioned lie within the four-year period mentioned in Section 11 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: The domestic participant has a loss from domestic business of 100,000 DM in year 1, in the same year an additional amount of 60,000 DM is to be set, so that a loss of 40,000 DM that can be carried forward remains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In year 2 there is a profit from domestic business operations of DM 200,000, from which DM 40,000 is deducted in accordance with Section 10d EStG, so that DM 160,000 is taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "(Without the additional amount for year 1, only DM 100,000 would have been taxed)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In year 3 there will be a distribution surplus of 40,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The distribution surplus is to be offset against the additional amount for year 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "That part of the tax is to be reimbursed which is due in year 2 to 40,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The reimbursement amount is in accordance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1123 to be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1126 The offsetting of the distribution surplus with the additional amounts (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1121 sentence 2) takes place at the rate at which the income from passive acquisition on which the additional amount is based has been converted (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10114)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "113 Tax reimbursement according to \u00a7 11 Paragraph 3 AStG1131 The principles of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "112 with the proviso that the reimbursement may in no case exceed the amount of the tax levied on the capital gain after offsetting any foreign taxes (maximum limit)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, no reimbursement is to be made if the capital gain is not taxable or if no tax was incurred in the year of the sale; the reimbursement is to be made according to the reduced tax rate if the tax relief according to \u00a7 34 EStG has been claimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the tax of the domestic participant has been reduced by allowing expenses in connection with the sale to be deducted, this also reduces the maximum amount of the reimbursement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1132 If an additional amount is to be recognized in the year of the sale, a taxable capital gain is not to be taken into account by reducing the additional amount (Section 11 Para Tax is the upper limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, this can be done in such a way that the capital gain is reduced by the additional amount, insofar as it is used for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1133 If the purchaser incurs a distribution surplus after the sale, a reimbursement of taxes of the seller according to Section 11 (2) AStG is excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "114 Distribution of profit shares in the case of interim income with the character of an investment they are thus finally subject to additional taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A reduction by profit distributions is out of the question (Section 11 (4) sentence 1 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Distributed profit shares, on the other hand, remain tax-free insofar as they do not exceed this investment-like interim income (Section 11 (4) sentence 2 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Example: Income of the foreign company in the 01 financial year - from active activity100 - from other passive acquisition within the meaning of Section 8 (1) AStG200- with capital investment character 400 Distribution in financial year 021000 The additional amount is 600 the income contained therein with capital investment character 400 The additional amount can only be a partial distribution from 200 (\u00a7 11 Paragraph 1 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 4 Sentence 1 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "An additional amount of 400 is therefore to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The distribution remains tax-free in the amount of 400 (Section 11 (4) sentence 2 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A tax refund in accordance with Section 11 (2) AStG for previous years is only possible for the remaining distribution of 400 (1000-200-400), because the distributions are no longer available for reimbursement purposes up to the amount of the interim investment income (Section 11 Paragraph 4 Clause 4 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the distribution in the 02 financial year is less than the total additional amount from the 01 financial year of the foreign company, there is no reduction up to the amount of the additional amount that is attributable to investment income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Only if the distribution exceeds this part of the additional amount, the portion of the additional amount that is attributable to income from other passive acquisitions must be reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "12 Tax credit121 Creditable taxes1211 According to \u00a7 12 AStG, all taxes that are not to be treated as business expenses can be credited to which the foreign company has been used with the income subject to additional taxation as well as with the assets on which this income is based"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Eligible are those listed in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10121 mentioned taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1212 In the context of \u00a7 12 AStG, German taxes on income, earnings and assets that the foreign company has paid (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the capital gains tax levied on profit distributions from German companies)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The corporation tax on the profit distributions of German corporations is not to be taken into account because this tax is not levied on the foreign company; such profit shares are possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to be excluded from the additional amount in accordance with Section 13 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1213 For the crediting, the total amount of creditable taxes is credited against the total income (corporation) tax from the additional amount; it is irrelevant how the interim income is made up according to origin and burden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1214 The BMF letter of 23 May 1980 (BStBl I 282) deals with the special situation with regard to Swiss taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Reference is made to the BFH rulings of 9 November 1983 BStBl 1984 II, 468 and of 12 July 1989 BStBl 1990 II, 113"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "122 Special cases1221 If the foreign company with interim income in which profit shares are to be reduced in accordance with Section 11 Paragraph 1 AStG or Section 13 AStG, this tax is fully creditable regardless of these reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax to be credited may also in this case be the German income or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Do not exceed corporation tax, which is proportionally attributable to the reduced additional amount (see BFH judgment of 9 November 1983 BStBl 1984 II, 468)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1222 If the company has mixed income, the part of the foreign tax that is attributable to the income subject to additional taxation can be offset (Section 34c EStG in conjunction with Section 12 (2) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxes are here in the corresponding application of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "834 split"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1223 The flat-rate provision of Section 34c (5) EStG is not applicable to interim income subject to additional taxation (BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 983)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "123 Credit for interim income with capital investment character1231 In accordance with Section 12 (3) AStG, foreign withholding taxes that apply to distributed profit shares that are tax-exempt according to Section 11 (4) sentence 2 AStG can be offset or deducted within the framework of additional taxation at the request of the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (1) and (2) EStG and Section 26 (1) and (6) sentence 1 KStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1232 Section 12 (3) sentence 2 AStG contains a separate correction provision for changing the notices in which the additional amount was taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "13 Box dividends 130 General Insofar as profit shares are to be excluded from the additional amount according to \u00a7 13 AStG, this is a factual tax exemption, so that this dividend deduction takes precedence over distributions by the intermediate company according to \u00a7 11 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "131 Box discount for foreign participations1311 According to \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 AStG, profit shares that are not already outside the additional taxation according to \u00a7 8 Paragraph 2 AStG and for which benefits for significant participations would be granted in the event of direct inflow to domestic participants are to be treated as follows: are deducted from the additional amount a) Profit shares from DBA countries for which a DBA box discount would be considered if they were received directly, b) Profit shares from countries within the meaning of Section 26 (3) KStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "5 KStDV, for which the preferential treatment of this provision (quasi-box privilege) would come into consideration in the event of direct inflow"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For profit shares from other countries, the tax levied on the additional amount is to be reduced in such a way that, in addition to the tax credit according to \u00a7 12 AStG, the indirect tax credit according to \u00a7 26 para 2 KStG is granted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The additional amount must be increased by this additional tax amount (Section 26 (2) sentence 5 KStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This increase does not apply to the trade tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of trade tax, the additional amount according to Section 13 (1) No. 2 AStG is to be reduced by profit shares that would be exempt from trade tax if they were paid directly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1312 Partial write-offs on investments are to be taken into account as reducing profits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "They are not to be added to the exempted box dividends (see BFH judgments of February 2, 1972 BStBl II, 397 and of September 19, 1973 BStBl II, 873)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Distribution-related depreciation of the partial value of participations is not to be taken into account when determining the profit of the foreign company, insofar as Section 8b (6) KStG applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1313 Insofar as the benefit under Section 26 (5) KStG is used for a box dividend received by the intermediate company, the benefit under Section 13 AStG cannot be granted for this dividend (Section 13 (1) sentence 2 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1314 The regulations of \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 AStG presuppose that the distributing companies exclude their gross income or almost exclusively from under \u00a7 8 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 6 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The principles to be observed in Section 26 (2) to (5) KStG apply accordingly (see Section 76 (8) and (9) KStR 1990)."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For profit distributions within the meaning of Section 13 (1) AStG and for the question of active activity, the relevant financial year is the year specified in the profit distribution resolution (see Section 76 (10) KStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If an abuse of design options is to be suspected in this regard, a decision must be made according to the circumstances of the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Was z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If an active activity was created for the company only for the year of the distribution - without economic reason - this structure is not recognized for tax purposes according to \u00a7 42 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "132 Box discount for domestic participations Profit shares from the Federal Republic of Germany, to which Section 13 (2) AStG applies, must be deducted from the added amount, without interruption for at least 12 months before the end of the assessment period or the different profit determination period of the unrestricted taxpayer for whom the added amount for the profit shares exists is deemed to have been received (Section 10 (2) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "133 Beneficiary capital gains 1331 Section 13 (3) AStG excludes profits that arise from the sale of participations in active foreign corporations (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1312) or at domestic corporations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 13 (3) AStG does not apply to losses that arise from such sales"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1332 The acquiring corporation belongs to the same group as the selling foreign company, if both companies are under the uniform management of a parent company (Section 18 AktG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is also a sale within the group if the acquiring corporation is the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A sale within the group does not exist, however, if z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the acquiring corporation does not come from the company forming the top of the group, but from a person behind it (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Sole shareholder)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1333 Section 13 (3) AStG is also not applicable if shares are temporarily transferred from the intermediate company to a company belonging to the group with a view to their final sale to a company outside the group"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Reference to \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 and 42 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1334 Compliance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "132, when applying the deadline rule according to Section 13 (2) last sentence AStG, always leads to preferential treatment due to a capital gain if the profit calculation periods of all parties do not differ from one another"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1335 If the selling share is a share in a domestic corporation, a limited tax liability of the foreign company resulting from the sale remains unaffected in accordance with Section 49 (1) No. 2 e EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "134 Calculation of the participation amount According to \u00a7 13 Abs 4 AStG the amount of the indirect participation of the tax resident in the downstream company is to be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted here that Section 13 (4) AStG is only based on participation in nominal capital"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The participation to be taken into account in accordance with Section 13 (4) AStG must be checked separately for each domestic participant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, his relevant participation in accordance with Section 13 (4) AStG cannot be added together with other participations directly or indirectly held by him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "135 Profit shares to be excluded The profit shares are to be excluded from the additional amount on proof with the amount with which they are included in the determination of income (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1002 and 1003) have been received, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "reduced by the expenses that are economically connected with them within the meaning of Section 10 (4) AStG and the tax on them that has been deducted in accordance with Section 10 (1) AStG when determining the additional amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "14 Downstream intermediate companies140 Scope 1401 The transferring attribution according to \u00a7 14 AStG takes effect if a foreign company (parent company) holds a stake in a foreign intermediate company (subsidiary) and both companies have unlimited taxpayers or persons within the meaning of \u00a7 2 AStG at the end of the relevant financial year Subsidiaries are directly or indirectly more than half involved (reference to no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "721)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Both companies do not need to be the same domestic participants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The participation of the respective parent company is to be taken into account with the proportion of which tax residents are directly or indirectly involved in it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 7 (4) AStG must be observed as far as the determination of the majority shareholding is concerned"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, shares taken into account in this way have no effect on the implementation of the transferred attribution (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1402 \u00a7 14 AStG does not apply if a participation in the subsidiary is directly attributable to an unrestricted taxpayer (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "based on \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 or 42 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, this is directly subject to additional taxation according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1403 The prerequisites for the transferring attribution according to \u00a7 14 AStG must be checked separately for each subsidiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1404 Insofar as there is interim income with the character of an investment, an allocation within the meaning of Section 14 (1) AStG takes place from a participation amount of 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "(Section 7 (6) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "141 Income from intermediate companies1411 All interim income is subject to the transferring attribution according to \u00a7 14 AStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "701)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1412 The transferring attribution does not extend to the income accruing to the downstream company from activities or objects that are under Section 8 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1 to 6 AStG; profit distributions within the meaning of Section 8 (2) AStG; profit distributions from other active companies, insofar as they would be excluded from the additional amount according to Section 13 AStG if the domestic participant were directly involved in the distributing company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1413 It must be checked separately for each subsidiary whether there is low taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the exemption limit provided for in \u00a7 9 AStG based on gross income (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "901) and the absolute exemption limit of DM 120,000 insofar as they relate to society as such"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the application of the absolute exemption limit of DM 120,000 with regard to the individual domestic participants, all interim income directly and via \u00a7 14 AStG must be added together for a domestic participant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "83 and 9 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1414 The income of the subsidiary company from passive acquisition, which is subject to attribution according to \u00a7 14 AStG, is to be determined according to \u00a7 10 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The following should be noted here: For the subsidiary company, its own determination of profits in accordance with No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "10311"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, the sub-company must create its own balance sheets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the determination, the taxes levied on the subsidiary company within the meaning of Section 10 (1) sentence 1 AStG must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 10 (1) sentence 3 AStG does not apply to the attribution according to Section 14 (1) AStG (BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1415 According to para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The result of the subsidiary company determined in 1414 is attributable to the parent company and is directly included in the attribution according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The attribution takes place at the time of its creation, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in the last logical second before the end of the financial year of the subsidiary company (see BFH judgment of 28 September 1988 BStBl 1989 II, 13)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If there is also an additional taxation in the country of the upstream intermediate company (currently"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in France, Japan, Canada, USA), the procedure is as follows: the question of whether there is low taxation is, according to Section 8 (3) AStG, only based on the taxation in the country of domicile of the downstream intermediate company; an access tax levied in the country of the upstream company is not to be taken into account; the access tax levied in the country of the upstream intermediate company can be offset against the German access tax according to \u00a7 12 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1416 Not only positive but also negative income of the lower company is to be attributed to the parent company; Section 10 (1) sentence 3 AStG does not apply to the transferring attribution (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Likewise, negative income of the parent company, which is not to be deducted from its profits according to Section 10 (3) sentence 5 AStG, can be offset with positive income of the subsidiary company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1417 Positive and negative income of the parent and subsidiary companies can only be recorded or added once"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "subtracted from"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, a profit of the subsidiary that is consumed by its loss deduction is not attributable to the parent company; a loss of the subsidiary that is taken into account by deducting losses from its profits is not deductible at the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Since the attribution within the meaning of Section 14 (1) AStG is designed as an independent legal consequence, the deduction at the subsidiary has priority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If a loss is made retrospectively (i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "in the lecture channels) is balanced with a profit, the requirement for its deduction at the parent company does not apply retrospectively"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The findings at the parent company are to be corrected accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "For the sake of simplification, it can be allowed that the loss deduction remains with the parent company and instead the loss is not deducted from the income of the subsidiary company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for this is that there are no significant tax effects"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Proceed accordingly in the case of loss carry-back"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1418 The transferring attribution does not take place if the share in the subsidiary company has already been attributed to an unrestricted taxpayer according to \u00a7\u00a7 39 41 or 42 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "142 Distributions of the subsidiary company to the parent company1421 According to \u00a7 14 AStG, income of the subsidiary company from passive acquisition through a transferring attribution to the domestic participants of the parent company proportionately into the addition taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The domestic participant has to re-tax this income if it is distributed by the subsidiary company and included in the additional taxation of the domestic participant as dividends received by the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A double charge is avoided by reducing the amount subject to the transferring attribution by such dividends and deducting the amounts attributed in the four previous years from the profit distributions, insofar as the profit distributions exceed the amount attributable according to Section 14 (1) AStG (distribution surplus)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1422 For the amount of the reduction and for the offsetting of the distribution surplus, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1111 and 1124 respectively"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The legal consequences of Section 11 AStG, even if applied accordingly, based on Section 14 (2) AStG, only come into effect in the calendar or financial year in which the attributable interim income is to be recognized as part of an additional amount according to Section 10 (2) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1423 The reductions according to para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1421 must be carried out separately for each subsidiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not permitted to offset the reduction amounts of a subsidiary with the amounts attributable to other subsidiaries"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1424 Section 11 AStG shall apply to interim income of a subsidiary company which, due to Section 14 AStG, is subject to the addition of a taxpayer under Section 7 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the additional amount must also be reduced by the profit distributions of the parent company to the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1425 Section 12 AStG is to be applied to interim income of a subsidiary company that is subject to addition under Section 7 AStG due to Section 14 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The following taxes are to be taken into account: Income and wealth taxes that the subsidiary company pays in its country of domicile or in other countries; capital gains taxes on distributions by the subsidiary company in the country of domicile; income and wealth taxes in the state of the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The crediting is to be carried out as if it were the controlling company's own taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The additional amount of the domestic participant must be increased by these taxes (Section 12 (1) sentence 2 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "143 Subsequent connection of further foreign companies If several sub-companies are connected after each other, the allocation according to \u00a7 14 Paragraph 1 and 3 AStG takes place in the last logical second of the respective financial year of the lowest downstream sub-company through all upstream sub-companies up to the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, it is not objectionable if, in the case of a different financial year of the companies standing one below the other, the transfer from the lower to the upper level is permitted in the last logical second of the financial year of the superordinate company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that this does not lead to serious time shifts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "144 Provisions of the Agreement on the Avoidance of Double Taxation1441 Intermediate income of downstream intermediate companies is included in the additional amount after being allocated to the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of the agreement to avoid double taxation with the country in which the parent company is domiciled shall apply accordingly (Section 10 (5) AStG); this can lead to the exemption of the additional amount in accordance with a DBA box discount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 14 (4) AStG restricts this exemption if the additional amount contains interim income that is to be allocated to the parent company in accordance with Section 14 (1) to (3) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, the exemption for the additional amount is only to be granted if it would be tax-exempt under the DTA even if the taxpayer had a direct interest in the subsidiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1442 Income that is subject to the transferring attribution is to be exempted in accordance with Section 10 (5) AStG if there is a box discount with regard to both the parent company and the company in which the interim income actually accrued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether other intermediary companies (Section 14 (3) AStG) have box discounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1443 If there is a box discount only with the state of the parent company, only that part of the additional amount to be assessed (AHZB) according to Section 10 (5) AStG that comes from the parent company's own income is to be released"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the part of the AHZB that comes from the transferring attribution of the subsidiary company is not to be exempted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If there is a box discount only with the state of the subsidiary company, an exemption according to Section 10 (5) AStG does not apply either to the parent company's own income or to the income of the downstream subsidiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1444 If the parent company benefiting from the box pays out profits and interim income of a subsidiary company is to be recorded in the additional amount by way of the transferring attribution and if it is not exempted under a DTA or Section 14 (4) AStG - i.e. taxable - the box dividends for residents are subject to the DTA Regulations on box discounts are tax-free and do not entitle these distributions to reduce the additional amount (Section 11 (1) AStG) or to refund taxes paid on additional amounts (Section 11 (2) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes that are levied on these distributions in the state of the parent company are to be deducted from the passive income of the subsidiary companies at the time of the distribution or to be offset in accordance with Section 12 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1445 If the non-box-beneficiary subsidiary pays out profits to the box-beneficiary parent company, these distributions as such at the parent company are not included in the addition or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Tax liability according to \u00a7 7 Abs 1 AStG (\u00a7 14 Abs 4 sentence 3 AStG) and do not entitle to reductions according to \u00a7 14 Abs 2 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 11 AStG (Section 14 (4) sentence 3 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes that are levied in the state of the subsidiary company and the parent company from these distributions of the subsidiary company are to be deducted from the passive income of the subsidiary company at the time of distribution in accordance with Section 10 Paragraph 1 AStG or offset against German taxes in accordance with Section 12 AStG (Section 14 Para 4 sentence 4 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1446 For losses incurred by the subsidiary or the parent company, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1416 and No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1417 1447 In the case of income from subsidiary companies that were generated in the financial years of the subsidiary companies that ended before January 1, 1980 and were subject to the transferring attribution, the application of Section 10 (5) AStG is solely based on the entitlement of the parent company (reference to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1052)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1448 According to \u00a7 14 AStG, the attributed interim income is treated like original income of the parent company, therefore attributed interim income with the character of an investment is the same as its own interim income with the nature of an investment of the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The protective effect of Section 10 (5) AStG is only retained in the case of interim income with the character of an investment if it does not prevail in either the subsidiary or the parent company (Section 10 (6) sentence 1 AStG a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "15 Family Foundations 151 Allocation of Income and Assets 1511 According to Section 15 AStG, income and assets of foreign family foundations are to be allocated directly to unrestricted taxable founders, beneficiaries or beneficiaries according to their share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of the double taxation agreement do not preclude attribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 15 AStG and \u00a7 20 EStG are mutually exclusive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 15 (1) and (4) AStG takes precedence over Section 22 (1) EStG (BFH judgment of February 2, 1994 BStBl II, 727)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Income is to be understood as that which would result if the family foundation were to assume unlimited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The determination of income and assets is based on the principles of German tax law, including the granting of lump sums and tax exemptions (see BFH rulings of 5 November 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 388 and of 2 February 1994 BStBl II, 727 R)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1512 For the purposes of income tax, the unlimited taxpayer is assigned the income that accrued to the family foundation for the relevant assessment period; for the purposes of wealth tax, the family foundation's assets on the relevant reference date"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1513 The attribution according to \u00a7 15 AStG also takes place if a) the founder was subject to limited tax liability at the time of establishment, b) the person subject to unlimited taxation is only entitled to accruals but not to draw"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1514 Income and assets of the family foundation are fully available to the founder during his unlimited or extended limited tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "due to death) to be allocated proportionally to the beneficiaries and beneficiaries"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1515 If the family foundation allocates income to a founder, beneficiary or beneficiary that has already been allocated to this person in accordance with Section 15 AStG, this donation is not subject to income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1516 If assets of the foundation have been assigned to a founder, beneficiary or beneficiary according to \u00a7 15 AStG, the beneficiary or beneficiary is not subject to wealth tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "152 Founder, beneficiary, beneficiary 1521 The founder is whoever established the foundation, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "for whose account the foundation business was concluded (BFH judgment of 5 November 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 388), or who, in the manner of the founder, transfers or transfers assets to the foundation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "the person to whom the foundation business can be assigned from an economic point of view"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The beneficiary is a person who, according to the statutes of the family foundation, receives or will receive pecuniary benefits from the foundation in the present or the future, or who, according to the statutes, can be expected to receive pecuniary benefits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The person entitled to contingency is a person who can legally request or actually effect the transfer of the foundation's assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of random destinaries, there is no attribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1522 An attribution takes place if the founder, his relatives and their descendants are entitled to more than half of the benefits or are entitled to a claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient if one or more descendants, alone or together, are entitled to more than half of the benefits or are entitled to accidents (BFH judgment of 5 November 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 388)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1523 If more than one person is entitled to receive or have an accident, the ratio of their entitlements to one another is decisive for the limit of Section 15 (2) and (3) AStG and for the distribution of income and assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "154 Equal treatment of other assets and associations A trust established abroad with no legal capacity can be an estate (BFH judgment of 5 November 1992 BStBl 1993 II, 388); a trust within the meaning of US law can also be special-purpose assets within the meaning of Section 15 (4) AStG (BFH judgment of February 2, 1994 BStBl II, 727)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "155 Extended limited taxpayers, tax credit, subsequent connection of intermediate companies 1551 If a person within the meaning of Section 2 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 No. 1 AStG (see Section 5 Paragraph 1 Sentence 1 AStG) is alone or together with other founders, beneficiaries or beneficiaries the extended limited taxable income and assets of the foundation (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "25 and 31) according to their share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This person's entitlement to benefit or seizure must be taken into account for the limit set out in Section 15 (2) and (3) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1552 The crediting of domestic and foreign taxes of the family foundation against the German taxes of the founders, beneficiaries or beneficiaries is based on \u00a7 12 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c EStG and Section 10 (1) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "12 is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the maximum amount to be calculated in accordance with Section 34c, Paragraph 1, Clause 2 of the Income Tax Act, the attributable income takes the place of the \"foreign income\" within the meaning of the provision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Taxes can only be credited for the years in which they were paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the assessment base for foreign income in Germany is lower than abroad, the creditable foreign tax is nevertheless to be applied in full when calculating the maximum amount in accordance with Section 34c (1) sentence 2 EStG, if no non-foreign income has been included in your foreign assessment base (BFH judgment of 2 February 1994 BStBl II, 727)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1553 If the family foundation has a stake in a foreign intermediate company, the stake is to be allocated to the founders, beneficiaries or beneficiaries according to their share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Sections 7 8 and 14 AStG are to be applied to the participation in the intermediate company as if each of these persons held the share attributable to them directly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "16 Obligation to cooperate 160 General Section 16 AStG lays down comprehensive disclosure of the taxpayer in business relationships with persons who are not or only insignificantly taxed abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of cross-border issues, the regulation extends the designation requirement according to Section 160 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Debts, other burdens, business expenses or business expenses can only be deducted if the existing relationships with the person abroad are fully disclosed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "With the disclosure obligation of \u00a7 16 AStG, \u00a7 90 paragraph 2 AO must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer must clarify the facts and obtain all necessary evidence; Above all, he must also fulfill his duty to provide evidence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The request of the tax authority according to \u00a7 16 AStG for disclosure does not constitute an administrative act (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl 1988 II, 927)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "161 Disclosure of foreign relations 1611 All taxpayers are obliged to disclose the debts or expenses in connection with business relations with foreign persons, which are not or only insignificantly taxed on the income from these business relations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the term \"business relationships\", the statements in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "14 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The business relationship can exist with a foreign company (see Section 7 (1) AStG) or a person or partnership based abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that they are related persons (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "within the meaning of \u00a7\u00a7 1 Paragraph 2 or 7 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1612 There is insignificant taxation of the income of foreign persons from their business relationships with the taxpayer if the income tax rate is less than 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "exists (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient that the insignificant taxation only applies to part of the income if the income from the business relationship in question belongs to it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that the income comes from passive acquisition within the meaning of Section 8 (1) AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1613 The taxpayer has only fulfilled his obligation to cooperate if he has disclosed all direct or indirect relationships that exist or have existed with the person abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This includes all facts that may be of importance for a tax assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer has to exhaust all legal and factual options available to him (see BFH judgment of 13 March 1985 BStBl 1986 II, 318)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "He must also create, obtain and secure evidence within the scope of the obligation to provide evidence (BFH judgment of 16 April 1980 BStBl 1981 II, 492)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The disclosure obligation also includes facts about the interested parties behind the foreign business partner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The naming of a domiciliary company as a business partner is just as insufficient as the declaration of the taxpayer that not he, but a third party stands behind the foreign company (see BFH decision of 25 August 1986 BStBl 1987 II, 481)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Uncertainties regarding the person of the creditor or recipient are at the expense of the taxpayer (see BFH judgment of 13 March 1985 BStBl 1986 II, 318 and BFH decision of 9 July 1986 BStBl 1987 II, 487)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Foreign prohibition norms do not mean that a disclosure request is disproportionate or unreasonable from the outset (see BFH judgment of 16 April 1980 BStBl 1981 II, 492)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1614 If the taxpayer does not fulfill his disclosure obligation, the asserted approach of debts or encumbrances or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "not to recognize the deduction of business expenses or business expenses according to \u00a7 160 AO; The tax authority does not have any further official investigation obligations arising from the breach of the duty to cooperate (see BFH decision of 9 July 1986 BStBl 1987 II, 487)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of acquisition or manufacturing processes that have to be capitalized, the acquisition or manufacturing costs are to be recognized as operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The fact that expenses actually occurred does not change the legal consequence of non-recognition (see BFH judgment of 29 November 1978 BStBl 1979 II, 587)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "162 Insurance in lieu of oath At the request of the tax authorities, the taxpayer can fulfill his disclosure obligation by giving an affirmation in lieu of oath that he is not or only to a limited extent in a position to disclose facts and that his information about certain Facts are correct and complete"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "There is no entitlement to issue an affidavit in lieu of an oath"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Assurances given in lieu of oath or self-declarations given without the request of the tax authorities are in themselves not a sufficient means of providing credibility"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "17 Clarification of the facts 171 Area of \u200b\u200bapplication 1711 In contrast to Section 16 AStG, which is only linked to Section 160 AO, Section 17 AStG only refers to the application of Sections 5 7 to 16 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The request for information according to \u00a7 17 AStG is an administrative act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1712 In order to apply Sections 7 to 14 AStG, every person with unlimited or extended limited tax liability involved in the intermediate company is obliged to clarify the facts and obtain the necessary evidence, in particular the documents specified in Section 17 (1) AStG (Section 90 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "He has to present all documents that are actually and legally accessible to him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In particular, he has to do everything to obtain clarification of the facts from the companies, their bodies or third parties by exercising his shareholder rights or his other legal and factual possibilities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If several are involved, they have to work together, especially by exercising their voting rights appropriately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The submission of balance sheets and income statements in accordance with Section 17 (1) AStG can also be appropriate to determine and verify an alleged low taxation (BFH judgment of 16 April 1986 BStBl II, 736)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1713 The parties involved cannot plead that they cannot fulfill their duty to cooperate if, depending on the circumstances of the case, they could have given them the opportunity to do so in the structuring of their circumstances (Section 90 (2) AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1714 The tax office can under the conditions of \u00a7\u00a7 93 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "and \u00a7 200 AO hear third parties as information person, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Persons who worked for the foreign company or who had a business relationship with it or who participated in the engagement of the foreign company on behalf or in the interests of a domestic party"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "According to \u00a7 97 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "AO to submit the necessary documents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If such persons are resident abroad, intergovernmental legal and administrative assistance must be used (Section 117 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1715 According to \u00a7\u00a7 94 and 95 AO, the tax office can demand that the domestic parties involved or the persons providing information give or take an oath statement about their information"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "confirm their statement by oath (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "162)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1716 The tax authorities make use of the existing international agreements on the international exchange of information and on delivery and enforcement assistance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18 Separate statement 181 Procedure, content and period 1811 Procedure 18111 The tax bases for the application of Sections 7 to 14 AStG are listed separately and, if necessary,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "also determined uniformly (\u00a7 18 AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the tax bases for the application of \u00a7 5 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18112 Are in the income attributable to the controlling company according to \u00a7 14 KStG according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "AStG contain taxable income, the notification according to \u00a7 18 AStG must be sent to the subsidiary company (BFH judgment of 29 August 1984 BStBl 1985 II, 119)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18113 The taxpayers involved are obliged to appoint a joint authorized recipient residing in Germany within the meaning of \u00a7\u00a7 179 and 183 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If such a person is not appointed, you can proceed according to Section 183 (1) sentence 3 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18114 Each of the taxpayers involved can appeal against the notification of assessment (cf. \u00a7 352 Abs 2 AO and \u00a7 48 Abs 2 FGO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "If the investment is held through a partnership (Section 7 (3) AStG), the separate determination made against the shareholders can only be challenged in accordance with Section 352 (2) AO (Section 48 (1) FGO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The need to inform those involved in accordance with Section 360 Paragraph 3 AO or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Reference is made to Section 60 (3) FGO (see BFH judgment of February 28, 1990 BStBl II, 696)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1812 Content of the separate statement 18121 All tax assessment bases are to be determined that can be independently significant for the taxation procedure of the domestic participant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "A special determination for the trade tax is not required if the tax bases for this tax result from the determined amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18122 In the notification of the separate determination (addition notification) it must be determined (see BFH judgment of 6 February 1985 II, 410) whether an addition is to be made; which persons are to be added according to Section 7 (1) AStG; what the attributable tax assessment bases are for the individual taxpayers; For what point in time the addition is justified according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG; to which upstream parent companies are interim income of downstream companies attributable (if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "a negative attribution notice is to be issued)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18123 According to \u00a7 18 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 AStG u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "to be determined separately (BFH judgment of July 17, 1985 BStBl 1986 II, 129): a) the taxes deductible according to \u00a7 10 paragraph 1 sentence 1 AStG, b) the income taxable according to \u00a7 7 paragraph 1 or paragraph 6 AStG, c) the income according to \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 a and No. 2 AStG to be excluded from the additional amount, d) the profit shares to be taken into account according to \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 b AStG and creditable foreign taxes, e) those according to \u00a7 11 Paragraph 1 AStG Addition amount to be reduced and f) the profit shares tax-free according to \u00a7 11 Paragraph 4 Sentence 2 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18124 For information purposes, a) the resulting distribution surplus, which can be carried back in accordance with Section 11 (2) AStG, b) the total amount of tax credits and c) the amount that is separate from trade tax (Section 13 (1) sentence 1 No. 2 AStG) is to be excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18125 The total amount of tax credit is made up of the respective share of the German and foreign taxes that are to be credited according to Section 12 (1) AStG; the foreign taxes paid on the profit shares tax-exempt under Section 11 (4) sentence 2 AStG (Section 12 (3) AStG) 3 the foreign corporation taxes that are to be taken into account in the case of box dividends in accordance with Section 13 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 b AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The total amount is to be offset in the assessment procedure like a foreign tax that has been levied on the additional amount to be applied (Section 12 (2) AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (1) EStG or Section 26 (1) KStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The German tax applicable to the additional amount must be determined for each additional amount as a whole and separately from other foreign income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18126 If it is found in a foreign company with mixed income that both the relative and the absolute exemption limit according to \u00a7 9 AStG are not exceeded, the absolute exemption limit of DM 120,000 may be exceeded for a participating tax resident if this is in several foreign companies is involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the application of \u00a7 9 AStG should be reserved in the notification of assessment (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868); Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "9024 remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In the case of Section 7 (6) sentence 2 AStG, the procedure is analogous"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18127 If the foreign company generates negative interim income, the losses must be determined separately (Section 10 (3) sentence 5 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 10d (3) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This determination is made in a separate procedure by the tax office, which determines the tax bases according to \u00a7 18 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18128 Questions relating to the taxation of domestic participants according to the provisions of the Income, Corporation and Trade Tax Act are not to be decided in the procedure under Section 18 AStG, but in the taxation procedure in which the established tax bases according to Section 182 (1) AO are included (see BFH judgment of April 20, 1988 BStBl II, 868)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Examples are: the inflow of profit shares (including hidden profit distributions), the fact that shares in the foreign company belong to business assets or private assets or the determination of the profit calculation period in which the added amount falls"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1813 Relevant financial year, year of assessment, assessment period 18131 The separate assessment is made for the calendar year in which the additional amount is deemed to have accrued in accordance with Section 10 (2) AStG (year of assessment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The interim income of a foreign company for a business year that corresponds to the calendar year must be declared and determined for the following calendar year (example: the 1992 business year is decisive for the year 1993); A financial year that deviates from the calendar year must be declared and determined for the calendar year in which the respective financial year ends (example: the 1991/92 financial year is decisive for the year 1992)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18132 The relationship between the relevant financial year, assessment year and assessment period of the taxpayer is shown in the following overview: Tax bases according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG Tax bases according to \u00a7 5 AStG Business year of the domestic participant Business year = calendar year Different business year Taxation always according to calendar year 1992 or 1992 Business year 1992 or 1992 Business year 1993 Business year 1993 (1992 if only limited taxpayers are involved; 1993 with simultaneous participation of unlimited taxpayers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": ") VZ 1993VZ 1993VZ 1992 Different financial year 1991 / 92Wy 1991 / 92Wy 1991 / 92Fstj 1992Fstj 1992Fstj 1992VZ 1992VZ 1992VZ 1992 or 1993 (1993 if the financial year of the foreign company ends after the end of the financial year of the domestic participant or if both financial years are the same"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise 1992) taxpayers are involved; 1993 with simultaneous participation of unlimited taxpayers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "2) 1993 if the business year of the foreign company ends after the end of the business year of the domestic participant or if both business years coincide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise 1992 1814 Downstream intermediate companies 18141 According to \u00a7 18 AStG, the tax bases of a downstream intermediate company (subcompany), whose interim income is to be allocated to another foreign company (parent company) according to \u00a7 14 AStG, are determined separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18122 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18142 A separate determination must be made for each subsidiary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It is u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "determine which positive or negative interim income is attributed to the parent company (see BFH judgment of February 6, 1985 BStBl II, 410) and, if residents are also directly involved in the subsidiary company, which positive interim income must be added to residents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Participants in the proceedings are the taxpayers subject to additional taxation who are directly or indirectly involved in the subsidiary; Item"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18111 to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18114 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18143 In the cases of Section 14 (3) AStG, the same procedure must be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1815 Refunds according to \u00a7 11 Abs 2 and 3 AStG 18151 The tax amount to be refunded according to \u00a7 11 Abs 2 and 3 AStG is determined in a special refund procedure, to which \u00a7 37 Abs 1 AO is applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The reimbursement is made by the tax office responsible for the addition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "It automatically determines the distributions received by the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "As far as these become known to the tax office, it will inform the tax office of the person obliged to add the amount of the distribution amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The reimbursement amount is determined by comparing income tax with and without taking into account the amount entitled to the reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The determinations of the tax bases in the previous notices have binding effect within the meaning of \u00a7 182 Abs 1 AO for the reimbursement procedure (see BFH judgment of July 17, 1985 BStBl 1986 II, 129)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18152 For reasons of simplicity, the original tax assessment can also be changed for the purpose of reimbursement in such a way that the additional amount to be applied is reduced by the amount that entitles the reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This may result in changes in the crediting of taxes according to \u00a7 12 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Even when an additional amount is taken into account for the first time, any distribution surplus that arises in later years can be deducted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "18153 For the reimbursement of trade tax, the tax office of the person obliged to add the tax will inform the responsible municipality of the tax bases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "182 Local competent tax office If several persons are involved in the foreign company within the meaning of \u00a7\u00a7 7 to 14 AStG and if several tax offices consider themselves locally responsible or not locally responsible or if there are other doubts about the local responsibility for the uniform and separate determination, determine the competent state tax authorities in cooperation with the Federal Office of Finance the local tax office responsible for the determination according to \u00a7 18 AStG (cf. BMF letter of 15 September 1975 BStBl I, 1018 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "183 Declaration on the separate and, if applicable,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "uniform determination 1831 Each of the unlimited taxpayers and extended limited taxpayers involved in the foreign company is required to submit a declaration for the separate and, if applicable,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "uniform determination required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "This obligation can be fulfilled by making a joint declaration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1832 The request to submit a declaration is made in the general request to submit annual tax returns"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The responsible tax office can also specifically request parties known to it to submit a declaration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "1833 In the procedure for the separate determination according to \u00a7 18 AStG, all information required to determine the tax bases must be provided and the necessary applications must be made (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "for the application of \u00a7 13 AStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "26 KStG required information and applications)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "20 Relationship to double taxation agreements 201 The application of additional taxation according to \u00a7\u00a7 7 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "AStG and the regulation on family foundations in \u00a7 15 AStG do not conflict with the double taxation agreements concluded by the Federal Republic of Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "202 Paragraph 20 (2) of the AStG puts foreign permanent establishments and partnerships on an equal footing with a foreign company insofar as they generate income of an investment nature"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, an exemption under the DTA is replaced by the crediting of foreign taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "Section 20 (2) AStG therefore only applies if the permanent establishment or partnership generates income of the nature of an investment, the income in the country in which it is located has an income tax rate of less than 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "and these are exempted due to a double taxation agreement in the Federal Republic of Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The provisions of Section 34c EStG and Section 26 KStG are to be applied accordingly for the crediting"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "203 Pursuant to Section 20 (3) AStG, the assets of a foreign permanent establishment (partnership) on which the income of a capital investment character is based are also changed from the exemption method to the credit method"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "The same applies on a pro-rata basis to equity holdings that corporations with unlimited tax liability hold in foreign intermediate companies, if they generate intermediate income with the character of capital investments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "However, the exemption method remains for assets based on investment income within the meaning of Section 10 (6) sentence 3 AStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124330.xml"}, "text": "21 Application Regulations The following table contains an overview of the temporal applic